var book = {
	"name": "2 Samuel",
	"numChapters": 24,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>After the death of Saul, when David had returned <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8024A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8024A\"></sup>from striking down the Amalekites, David remained two days in Ziklag.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And on the third day, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8025B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8025B\"></sup>a man came from Saul's camp, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8025C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8025C\"></sup>with his clothes torn and dirt on his head. And when he came to David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8025D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8025D\"></sup>he fell to the ground and paid homage.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>David said to him, “Where do you come from?” And he said to him, “I have escaped from the camp of Israel.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And David said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8027E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8027E\"></sup>“How did it go? Tell me.” And he answered, “The people fled from the battle, and also many of the people have fallen and are dead, and Saul and his son Jonathan are also dead.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then David said to the young man who told him, “How do you know that Saul and his son Jonathan are dead?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the young man who told him said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8029F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8029F\"></sup>“By chance I happened to be on Mount Gilboa, and there was Saul leaning on his spear, and behold, the chariots and the horsemen were close upon him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And when he looked behind him, he saw me, and called to me. And I answered, ‘Here I am.’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he said to me, ‘Who are you?’ I answered him, ‘I am an Amalekite.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And he said to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8032G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8032G\"></sup>‘Stand beside me and kill me, for anguish has seized me, and yet my life still lingers.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So I stood beside him and killed him, because I was sure that he could not live after he had fallen. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8033H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8033H\"></sup>And I took the crown that was on his head and the armlet that was on his arm, and I have brought them here to my lord.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then David took hold of his clothes and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8034I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8034I\"></sup>tore them, and so did all the men who were with him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And they mourned and wept <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8035J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8035J\"></sup>and fasted until evening for Saul and for Jonathan his son and for the people of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for the house of Israel, because they had fallen by the sword.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And David said to the young man who told him, “Where do you come from?” And he answered, “I am the son of a sojourner, an Amalekite.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>David said to him, “How is it you were not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8037K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8037K\"></sup>afraid to put out your hand to destroy <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8037L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8037L\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s anointed?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8038M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8038M\"></sup>David called one of the young men and said, “Go, execute him.” And he struck him down so that he died.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And David said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8039N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8039N\"></sup>“Your blood be on your head, for your own mouth has testified against you, saying, ‘I have killed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8039O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8039O\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s anointed.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8040P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8040P\"></sup>lamented with this lamentation over Saul and Jonathan his son,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and he said it should be taught to the people of Judah; behold, it is written in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8041Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8041Q\"></sup>the Book of Jashar. He said:",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Your glory, O Israel, is slain on your high places!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8042R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8042R\"></sup>How the mighty have fallen!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8043S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8043S\"></sup>Tell it not in Gath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8043T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8043T\"></sup>publish it not in the streets of Ashkelon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8043U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8043U\"></sup>lest the daughters of the Philistines rejoice,lest the daughters of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8043V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8043V\"></sup>the uncircumcised exult.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8044W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8044W\"></sup>“You mountains of Gilboa,let there be no dew or rain upon you,nor fields of offerings!For there the shield of the mighty was defiled,the shield of Saul, not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8044X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8044X\"></sup>anointed with oil.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“From the blood of the slain,from the fat of the mighty,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8045Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8045Y\"></sup>the bow of Jonathan turned not back,and the sword of Saul returned not empty.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Saul and Jonathan, beloved and lovely!In life and in death they were not divided;they were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8046Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8046Z\"></sup>swifter than eagles;they were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8046AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8046AA\"></sup>stronger than lions.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“You daughters of Israel, weep over Saul,who clothed you luxuriously in scarlet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8047AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8047AB\"></sup>who put ornaments of gold on your apparel.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8048AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8048AC\"></sup>“How the mighty have fallenin the midst of the battle!“Jonathan lies slain on your high places.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>I am distressed for you, my brother Jonathan;very pleasant have you been to me;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8049AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8049AD\"></sup>your love to me was extraordinary,surpassing the love of women.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8050AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8050AE\"></sup>“How the mighty have fallen,and the weapons of war perished!”"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>After this David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8051A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8051A\"></sup>inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Shall I go up into any of the cities of Judah?” And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Go up.” David said, “To which shall I go up?” And he said, “To <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8051B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8051B\"></sup>Hebron.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So David went up there, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8052C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8052C\"></sup>his two wives also, Ahinoam of Jezreel and Abigail the widow of Nabal of Carmel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And David brought up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8053D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8053D\"></sup>his men who were with him, everyone with his household, and they lived in the towns of Hebron.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the men of Judah came, and there they anointed David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8054E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8054E\"></sup>king over the house of Judah.When they told David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8054F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8054F\"></sup>“It was the men of Jabesh-gilead who buried Saul,”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>David sent messengers to the men of Jabesh-gilead and said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8055G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8055G\"></sup>“May you be blessed by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, because you showed this loyalty to Saul your lord and buried him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> show steadfast love and faithfulness to you. And I will do good to you because you have done this thing.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now therefore let your hands be strong, and be valiant, for Saul your lord is dead, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8057H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8057H\"></sup>the house of Judah has anointed me king over them.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8058I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8058I\"></sup>Abner the son of Ner, commander of Saul's army, took Ish-bosheth the son of Saul and brought him over to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8058J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8058J\"></sup>Mahanaim,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and he made him king over Gilead and the Ashurites and Jezreel and Ephraim and Benjamin and all Israel.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Ish-bosheth, Saul's son, was forty years old when he began to reign over Israel, and he reigned two years. But the house of Judah followed David.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8061K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8061K\"></sup>And the time that David was king in Hebron over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8061L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8061L\"></sup>the house of Judah was seven years and six months.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Abner the son of Ner, and the servants of Ish-bosheth the son of Saul, went out from Mahanaim to Gibeon.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Joab the son of Zeruiah and the servants of David went out and met them at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8063M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8063M\"></sup>the pool of Gibeon. And they sat down, the one on the one side of the pool, and the other on the other side of the pool.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And Abner said to Joab, “Let the young men arise and compete before us.” And Joab said, “Let them arise.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then they arose and passed over by number, twelve for Benjamin and Ish-bosheth the son of Saul, and twelve of the servants of David.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And each caught his opponent by the head and thrust his sword in his opponent's side, so they fell down together. Therefore that place was called Helkath-hazzurim, which is at Gibeon.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the battle was very fierce that day. And Abner and the men of Israel were beaten before the servants of David.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8068N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8068N\"></sup>three sons of Zeruiah were there, Joab, Abishai, and Asahel. Now Asahel was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8068O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8068O\"></sup>as swift of foot as a wild gazelle.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And Asahel pursued Abner, and as he went, he turned neither to the right hand nor to the left from following Abner.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Abner looked behind him and said, “Is it you, Asahel?” And he answered, “It is I.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Abner said to him, “Turn aside to your right hand or to your left, and seize one of the young men and take his spoil.” But Asahel would not turn aside from following him.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Abner said again to Asahel, “Turn aside from following me. Why should I strike you to the ground? How then could I lift up my face to your brother Joab?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But he refused to turn aside. Therefore Abner struck him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8073P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8073P\"></sup>in the stomach with the butt of his spear, so that the spear came out at his back. And he fell there and died where he was. And all who came to the place where Asahel had fallen and died, stood still.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But Joab and Abishai pursued Abner. And as the sun was going down they came to the hill of Ammah, which lies before Giah on the way to the wilderness of Gibeon.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And the people of Benjamin gathered themselves together behind Abner and became one group and took their stand on the top of a hill.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then Abner called to Joab, “Shall the sword devour forever? Do you not know that the end will be bitter? How long will it be before you tell your people to turn from the pursuit of their brothers?”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And Joab said, “As God lives, if <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8077Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8077Q\"></sup>you had not spoken, surely the men would not have given up the pursuit of their brothers until the morning.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Joab blew the trumpet, and all the men stopped and pursued Israel no more, nor did they fight anymore.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And Abner and his men went all that night through <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8079R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8079R\"></sup>the Arabah. They crossed the Jordan, and marching the whole morning, they came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8079S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8079S\"></sup>Mahanaim.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Joab returned from the pursuit of Abner. And when he had gathered all the people together, there were missing from David's servants nineteen men besides Asahel.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But the servants of David had struck down of Benjamin 360 of Abner's men.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And they took up Asahel and buried him in the tomb of his father, which was at Bethlehem. And Joab and his men marched all night, and the day broke upon them at Hebron."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>There was a long war between the house of Saul and the house of David. And David grew stronger and stronger, while the house of Saul became weaker and weaker.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8084A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8084A\"></sup>And sons were born to David at Hebron: his firstborn was Amnon, of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8084B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8084B\"></sup>Ahinoam of Jezreel;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and his second, Chileab, of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8085C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8085C\"></sup>Abigail the widow of Nabal of Carmel; and the third, Absalom the son of Maacah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8085D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8085D\"></sup>the daughter of Talmai king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8085E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8085E\"></sup>Geshur;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and the fourth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8086F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8086F\"></sup>Adonijah the son of Haggith; and the fifth, Shephatiah the son of Abital;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and the sixth, Ithream, of Eglah, David's wife. These were born to David in Hebron.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>While there was war between the house of Saul and the house of David, Abner was making himself strong in the house of Saul.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now Saul had a concubine whose name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8089G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8089G\"></sup>Rizpah, the daughter of Aiah. And Ish-bosheth said to Abner, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8089H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8089H\"></sup>“Why have you gone in to my father's concubine?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Abner was very angry over the words of Ish-bosheth and said, “Am I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8090I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8090I\"></sup>a dog's head of Judah? To this day I keep showing steadfast love to the house of Saul your father, to his brothers, and to his friends, and have not given you into the hand of David. And yet you charge me today with a fault concerning a woman.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8091J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8091J\"></sup>God do so to Abner and more also, if I do not accomplish for David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8091K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8091K\"></sup>what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sworn to him,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>to transfer the kingdom from the house of Saul and set up the throne of David over Israel and over Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8092L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8092L\"></sup>from Dan to Beersheba.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Ish-bosheth could not answer Abner another word, because he feared him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Abner sent messengers to David on his behalf, saying, “To whom does the land belong? Make your covenant with me, and behold, my hand shall be with you to bring over all Israel to you.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And he said, “Good; I will make a covenant with you. But one thing I require of you; that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8095M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8095M\"></sup>you shall not see my face unless you first bring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8095N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8095N\"></sup>Michal, Saul's daughter, when you come to see my face.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then David sent messengers to Ish-bosheth, Saul's son, saying, “Give me my wife Michal, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8096O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8096O\"></sup>for whom I paid the bridal price of a hundred foreskins of the Philistines.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Ish-bosheth sent and took her from her husband Paltiel the son of Laish.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But her husband went with her, weeping after her all the way to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8098P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8098P\"></sup>Bahurim. Then Abner said to him, “Go, return.” And he returned.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And Abner conferred with the elders of Israel, saying, “For some time past you have been seeking David as king over you.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now then bring it about, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8100Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8100Q\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has promised David, saying, ‘By the hand of my servant David I will save my people Israel from the hand of the Philistines, and from the hand of all their enemies.’”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Abner also spoke to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8101R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8101R\"></sup>Benjamin. And then Abner went to tell David at Hebron all that Israel and the whole house of Benjamin thought good to do.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Abner came with twenty men to David at Hebron, David made a feast for Abner and the men who were with him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Abner said to David, “I will arise and go and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8103S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8103S\"></sup>will gather all Israel to my lord the king, that they may make a covenant with you, and that you may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8103T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8103T\"></sup>reign over all that your heart desires.” So David sent Abner away, and he went in peace.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Just then the servants of David arrived with Joab from a raid, bringing much spoil with them. But Abner was not with David at Hebron, for he had sent him away, and he had gone in peace.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When Joab and all the army that was with him came, it was told Joab, “Abner the son of Ner came to the king, and he has let him go, and he has gone in peace.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Joab went to the king and said, “What have you done? Behold, Abner came to you. Why is it that you have sent him away, so that he is gone?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You know that Abner the son of Ner came to deceive you and to know <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8107U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8107U\"></sup>your going out and your coming in, and to know all that you are doing.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When Joab came out from David's presence, he sent messengers after Abner, and they brought him back from the cistern of Sirah. But David did not know about it.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And when Abner returned to Hebron, Joab took him aside into the midst of the gate to speak with him privately, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8109V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8109V\"></sup>and there he struck him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8109W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8109W\"></sup>in the stomach, so that he died, for the blood of Asahel his brother.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Afterward, when David heard of it, he said, “I and my kingdom are forever guiltless before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for the blood of Abner the son of Ner.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8111X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8111X\"></sup>May it fall upon the head of Joab and upon all his father's house, and may the house of Joab never be without <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8111Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8111Y\"></sup>one who has a discharge or who is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8111Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8111Z\"></sup>leprous or who holds a spindle or who falls by the sword or who lacks bread!”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So Joab and Abishai his brother killed Abner, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8112AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8112AA\"></sup>he had put their brother Asahel to death in the battle at Gibeon.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then David said to Joab and to all the people who were with him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8113AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8113AB\"></sup>“Tear your clothes and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8113AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8113AC\"></sup>put on sackcloth and mourn before Abner.” And King David followed the bier.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They buried Abner at Hebron. And the king lifted up his voice and wept at the grave of Abner, and all the people wept.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And the king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8115AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8115AD\"></sup>lamented for Abner, saying,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8115AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8115AE\"></sup>“Should Abner die <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8115AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8115AF\"></sup>as a fool dies?",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Your hands were not bound;your feet were not fettered;as one falls before the wickedyou have fallen.”And all the people wept again over him.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then all the people came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8117AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8117AG\"></sup>to persuade David to eat bread while it was yet day. But David swore, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8117AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8117AH\"></sup>“God do so to me and more also, if I taste bread or anything else <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8117AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8117AI\"></sup>till the sun goes down!”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And all the people took notice of it, and it pleased them, as everything that the king did pleased all the people.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>So all the people and all Israel understood that day that it had not been the king's will to put to death Abner the son of Ner.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And the king said to his servants, “Do you not know that a prince and a great man has fallen this day in Israel?",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And I was gentle today, though anointed king. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8121AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8121AJ\"></sup>These men, the sons of Zeruiah, are more severe than I. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8121AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8121AK\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> repay the evildoer according to his wickedness!”"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>When Ish-bosheth, Saul's son, heard that Abner had died at Hebron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8122A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8122A\"></sup>his courage failed, and all Israel was dismayed.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now Saul's son had two men who were captains of raiding bands; the name of the one was Baanah, and the name of the other Rechab, sons of Rimmon a man of Benjamin from Beeroth (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8123B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8123B\"></sup>for Beeroth also is counted part of Benjamin;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8124C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8124C\"></sup>the Beerothites fled <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8124D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8124D\"></sup>to Gittaim and have been sojourners there to this day).",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8125E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8125E\"></sup>Jonathan, the son of Saul, had a son who was crippled in his feet. He was five years old when the news about Saul and Jonathan <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8125F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8125F\"></sup>came from Jezreel, and his nurse took him up and fled, and as she fled in her haste, he fell and became lame. And his name was Mephibosheth.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now the sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, Rechab and Baanah, set out, and about the heat of the day they came to the house of Ish-bosheth as he was taking his noonday rest.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And they came into the midst of the house as if to get wheat, and they stabbed him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8127G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8127G\"></sup>in the stomach. Then Rechab and Baanah his brother escaped.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When they came into the house, as he lay on his bed in his bedroom, they struck him and put him to death and beheaded him. They took his head and went by the way of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8128H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8128H\"></sup>the Arabah all night,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and brought the head of Ish-bosheth to David at Hebron. And they said to the king, “Here is the head of Ish-bosheth, the son of Saul, your enemy, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8129I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8129I\"></sup>who sought your life. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has avenged my lord the king this day on Saul and on his offspring.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But David answered Rechab and Baanah his brother, the sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8130J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8130J\"></sup>“As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8130K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8130K\"></sup>who has redeemed my life out of every adversity,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8131L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8131L\"></sup>when one told me, ‘Behold, Saul is dead,’ and thought he was bringing good news, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8131M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8131M\"></sup>I seized him and killed him at Ziklag, which was the reward I gave him for his news.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>How much more, when wicked men have killed a righteous man in his own house on his bed, shall I not now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8132N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8132N\"></sup>require his blood at your hand and destroy you from the earth?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And David commanded his young men, and they killed them and cut off their hands and feet and hanged them beside the pool at Hebron. But they took the head of Ish-bosheth and buried it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8133O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8133O\"></sup>in the tomb of Abner at Hebron."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Then all the tribes of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8134A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8134A\"></sup>came to David at Hebron and said, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8134B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8134B\"></sup>we are your bone and flesh.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>In times past, when Saul was king over us, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8135C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8135C\"></sup>it was you who led out and brought in Israel. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8135D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8135D\"></sup>‘You shall be shepherd of my people Israel, and you shall be prince over Israel.’”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So all the elders of Israel came to the king at Hebron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8136E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8136E\"></sup>and King David made a covenant with them at Hebron <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8136F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8136F\"></sup>before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and they anointed David king over Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>David was thirty years old when he began to reign, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8137G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8137G\"></sup>he reigned forty years.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8138H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8138H\"></sup>At Hebron he reigned over Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8138I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8138I\"></sup>seven years and six months, and at Jerusalem he reigned over all Israel and Judah thirty-three years.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8139J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8139J\"></sup>And the king and his men went to Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8139K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8139K\"></sup>against the Jebusites, the inhabitants of the land, who said to David, “You will not come in here, but the blind and the lame will ward you off”—thinking, “David cannot come in here.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Nevertheless, David took the stronghold of Zion, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8140L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8140L\"></sup>that is, the city of David.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And David said on that day, “Whoever would strike the Jebusites, let him get up the water shaft to attack ‘the lame and the blind,’ who are hated by David's soul.” Therefore it is said, “The blind and the lame shall not come into the house.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And David lived in the stronghold and called it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8142M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8142M\"></sup>the city of David. And David built the city all around from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8142N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8142N\"></sup>Millo inward.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And David became greater and greater, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of hosts, was with him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8144O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8144O\"></sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8144P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8144P\"></sup>Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David, and cedar trees, also carpenters and masons who built David a house.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And David knew that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had established him king over Israel, and that he had exalted his kingdom for the sake of his people Israel.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And David took more <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8146Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8146Q\"></sup>concubines and wives from Jerusalem, after he came from Hebron, and more sons and daughters were born to David.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8147R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8147R\"></sup>And these are the names of those who were born to him in Jerusalem: Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Solomon,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Ibhar, Elishua, Nepheg, Japhia,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Elishama, Eliada, and Eliphelet.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When the Philistines heard that David had been anointed king over Israel, all the Philistines went up to search for David. But David heard of it and went down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8150S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8150S\"></sup>to the stronghold.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now the Philistines had come and spread out in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8151T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8151T\"></sup>the Valley of Rephaim.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8152U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8152U\"></sup>inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Shall I go up against the Philistines? Will you give them into my hand?” And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to David, “Go up, for I will certainly give the Philistines into your hand.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And David came to Baal-perazim, and David defeated them there. And he said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has broken through my enemies before me like a breaking flood.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8153V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8153V\"></sup>Therefore the name of that place is called Baal-perazim.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the Philistines left their idols there, and David and his men carried them away.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And the Philistines came up yet again <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8155W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8155W\"></sup>and spread out in the Valley of Rephaim.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8156X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8156X\"></sup>And when David inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he said, “You shall not go up; go around to their rear, and come against them opposite the balsam trees.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8157Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8157Y\"></sup>when you hear the sound of marching in the tops of the balsam trees, then rouse yourself, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8157Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8157Z\"></sup>for then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has gone out before you to strike down the army of the Philistines.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And David did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded him, and struck down the Philistines from Geba <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8158AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8158AA\"></sup>to Gezer."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8159A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8159A\"></sup>David again gathered all the chosen men of Israel, thirty thousand.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And David arose and went with all the people who were with him from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8160B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8160B\"></sup>Baale-judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8160C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8160C\"></sup>to bring up from there the ark of God, which is called by the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8160D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8160D\"></sup>who sits enthroned on the cherubim.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And they carried the ark of God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8161E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8161E\"></sup>on a new cart and brought it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8161F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8161F\"></sup>out of the house of Abinadab, which was on the hill. And Uzzah and Ahio, the sons of Abinadab, were driving the new cart,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>with the ark of God, and Ahio went before the ark.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And David and all the house of Israel were celebrating before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8163G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8163G\"></sup>songs and lyres and harps and tambourines and castanets and cymbals.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And when they came to the threshing floor of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8164H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8164H\"></sup>Nacon, Uzzah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8164I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8164I\"></sup>put out his hand to the ark of God and took hold of it, for the oxen stumbled.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was kindled against Uzzah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8165J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8165J\"></sup>God struck him down there because of his error, and he died there beside the ark of God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And David was angry because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had broken out against Uzzah. And that place is called Perez-uzzah to this day.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And David was afraid of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that day, and he said, “How can the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> come to me?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So David was not willing to take the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> into the city of David. But David took it aside <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8168K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8168K\"></sup>to the house of Obed-edom the Gittite.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> remained in the house of Obed-edom the Gittite three months, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8169L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8169L\"></sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blessed Obed-edom and all his household.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And it was told King David, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed the household of Obed-edom and all that belongs to him, because of the ark of God.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8170M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8170M\"></sup>So David went and brought up the ark of God from the house of Obed-edom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8170N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8170N\"></sup>to the city of David with rejoicing.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8171O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8171O\"></sup>those who bore the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had gone six steps, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8171P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8171P\"></sup>he sacrificed an ox and a fattened animal.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8172Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8172Q\"></sup>danced before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with all his might. And David was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8172R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8172R\"></sup>wearing a linen ephod.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So David and all the house of Israel brought up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with shouting and with the sound of the horn.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>As the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came into the city of David, Michal the daughter of Saul looked out of the window and saw King David leaping and dancing before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and she despised him in her heart.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And they brought in the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and set it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8175S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8175S\"></sup>in its place, inside the tent that David had pitched for it. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8175T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8175T\"></sup>And David offered burnt offerings and peace offerings before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And when David had finished offering the burnt offerings and the peace offerings, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8176U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8176U\"></sup>he blessed the people in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and distributed among all the people, the whole multitude of Israel, both men and women, a cake of bread, a portion of meat, and a cake of raisins to each one. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8177V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8177V\"></sup>Then all the people departed, each to his house.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And David returned to bless his household. But Michal the daughter of Saul came out to meet David and said, “How the king of Israel honored himself today, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8178W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8178W\"></sup>uncovering himself today before the eyes of his servants' female servants, as one of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8178X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8178X\"></sup>vulgar fellows shamelessly uncovers himself!”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And David said to Michal, “It was before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8179Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8179Y\"></sup>who chose me above your father and above all his house, to appoint me as prince over Israel, the people of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—and I will celebrate before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I will make myself yet more contemptible than this, and I will be abased in your eyes. But by the female servants of whom you have spoken, by them I shall be held in honor.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And Michal the daughter of Saul had no child to the day of her death."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8182A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8182A\"></sup>Now when the king lived in his house and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8182B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8182B\"></sup>had given him rest from all his surrounding enemies,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>the king said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8183C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8183C\"></sup>Nathan the prophet, “See now, I dwell <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8183D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8183D\"></sup>in a house of cedar, but the ark of God dwells <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8183E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8183E\"></sup>in a tent.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Nathan said to the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8184F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8184F\"></sup>“Go, do all that is in your heart, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But that same night the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Nathan,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Go and tell my servant David, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8186G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8186G\"></sup>Would you build me a house to dwell in?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I have not lived in a house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8187H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8187H\"></sup>since the day I brought up the people of Israel from Egypt to this day, but I have been moving about <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8187I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8187I\"></sup>in a tent for my dwelling.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>In all places where <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8188J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8188J\"></sup>I have moved with all the people of Israel, did I speak a word with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8188K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8188K\"></sup>any of the judges of Israel, whom I commanded <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8188L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8188L\"></sup>to shepherd my people Israel, saying, “Why have you not built me a house of cedar?”’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now, therefore, thus you shall say to my servant David, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8189M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8189M\"></sup>I took you from the pasture, from following the sheep, that you should be prince over my people Israel.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8190N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8190N\"></sup>And I have been with you wherever you went and have cut off all your enemies from before you. And I will make for you a great name, like the name of the great ones of the earth.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And I will appoint a place for my people Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8191O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8191O\"></sup>and will plant them, so that they may dwell in their own place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8191P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8191P\"></sup>and be disturbed no more. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8191Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8191Q\"></sup>And violent men shall afflict them no more, as formerly,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8192R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8192R\"></sup>from the time that I appointed judges over my people Israel. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8192S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8192S\"></sup>I will give you rest from all your enemies. Moreover, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> declares to you that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8192T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8192T\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will make you a house.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8193U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8193U\"></sup>When your days are fulfilled and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8193V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8193V\"></sup>you lie down with your fathers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8193W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8193W\"></sup>I will raise up your offspring after you, who shall come from your body, and I will establish his kingdom.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8194X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8194X\"></sup>He shall build a house for my name, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8194Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8194Y\"></sup>I will establish the throne of his kingdom forever.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8195Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8195Z\"></sup>I will be to him a father, and he shall be to me a son. When he commits iniquity, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8195AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8195AA\"></sup>I will discipline him with the rod of men, with the stripes of the sons of men,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8196AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8196AB\"></sup>but my steadfast love will not depart from him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8196AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8196AC\"></sup>as I took it from Saul, whom I put away from before you.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8197AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8197AD\"></sup>And your house and your kingdom shall be made sure forever before me. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8197AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8197AE\"></sup>Your throne shall be established forever.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>In accordance with all these words, and in accordance with all this vision, Nathan spoke to David.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then King David went in and sat before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8199AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8199AF\"></sup>“Who am I, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, and what is my house, that you have brought me thus far?",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And yet this was a small thing in your eyes, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8200AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8200AG\"></sup>You have spoken also of your servant's house for a great while to come, and this is instruction for mankind, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And what more can David say to you? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8201AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8201AH\"></sup>For you know your servant, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>!",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Because of your promise, and according to your own heart, you have brought about all this greatness, to make your servant know it.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8203AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8203AI\"></sup>Therefore you are great, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8203AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8203AJ\"></sup>For there is none like you, and there is no God besides you, according to all that we have heard with our ears.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8204AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8204AK\"></sup>And who is like your people Israel, the one nation on earth whom God went to redeem to be his people, making himself a name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8204AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8204AL\"></sup>and doing for them great and awesome things by driving out before your people, whom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8204AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8204AM\"></sup>you redeemed for yourself from Egypt, a nation and its gods?",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8205AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8205AN\"></sup>And you established for yourself your people Israel to be your people forever. And you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, became their God.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, confirm forever the word that you have spoken concerning your servant and concerning his house, and do as you have spoken.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And your name will be magnified forever, saying, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts is God over Israel,’ and the house of your servant David will be established before you.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>For you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts, the God of Israel, have made this revelation to your servant, saying, ‘I will build you a house.’ Therefore your servant has found courage to pray this prayer to you.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And now, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, you are God, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8209AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8209AO\"></sup>your words are true, and you have promised this good thing to your servant.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now therefore may it please you to bless the house of your servant, so that it may continue forever before you. For you, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, have spoken, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8210AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8210AP\"></sup>and with your blessing shall the house of your servant be blessed forever.”"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8211A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8211A\"></sup>After this David defeated the Philistines and subdued them, and David took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8211B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8211B\"></sup>Metheg-ammah out of the hand of the Philistines.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8212C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8212C\"></sup>And he defeated Moab and he measured them with a line, making them lie down on the ground. Two lines he measured to be put to death, and one full line to be spared. And the Moabites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8212D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8212D\"></sup>became servants to David and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8212E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8212E\"></sup>brought tribute.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>David also defeated <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8213F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8213F\"></sup>Hadadezer the son of Rehob, king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8213G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8213G\"></sup>Zobah, as he went to restore his power at the river Euphrates.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8214H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8214H\"></sup>And David took from him 1,700 horsemen, and 20,000 foot soldiers. And David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8214I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8214I\"></sup>hamstrung all the chariot horses but left enough for 100 chariots.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8215J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8215J\"></sup>And when the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8215K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8215K\"></sup>Syrians of Damascus came to help <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8215L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8215L\"></sup>Hadadezer king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8215M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8215M\"></sup>Zobah, David struck down 22,000 men of the Syrians.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then David put garrisons in Aram of Damascus, and the Syrians <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8216N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8216N\"></sup>became servants to David and brought tribute. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8216O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8216O\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave victory to David wherever he went.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And David took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8217P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8217P\"></sup>the shields of gold that were carried by the servants of Hadadezer and brought them to Jerusalem.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And from Betah and from Berothai, cities of Hadadezer, King David took very much bronze.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When Toi king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8219Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8219Q\"></sup>Hamath heard that David had defeated the whole army of Hadadezer,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Toi sent his son Joram to King David, to ask about his health and to bless him because he had fought against Hadadezer and defeated him, for Hadadezer had often been at war with Toi. And Joram brought with him articles of silver, of gold, and of bronze.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8221R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8221R\"></sup>These also King David dedicated to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, together with the silver and gold that he dedicated from all the nations he subdued,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>from Edom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8222S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8222S\"></sup>Moab, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8222T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8222T\"></sup>the Ammonites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8222U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8222U\"></sup>the Philistines, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8222V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8222V\"></sup>Amalek, and from the spoil of Hadadezer the son of Rehob, king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8222W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8222W\"></sup>Zobah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And David made a name for himself when he returned from striking down 18,000 Edomites in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8223X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8223X\"></sup>the Valley of Salt.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he put garrisons in Edom; throughout all Edom he put garrisons, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8224Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8224Y\"></sup>and all the Edomites became David's servants. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave victory to David wherever he went.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So David reigned over all Israel. And David administered justice and equity to all his people.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8226Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8226Z\"></sup>Joab the son of Zeruiah was over the army, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8226AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8226AA\"></sup>Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud was recorder,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8227AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8227AB\"></sup>Zadok the son of Ahitub and Ahimelech the son of Abiathar were priests, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8227AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8227AC\"></sup>Seraiah was secretary,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8228AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8228AD\"></sup>Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8228AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8228AE\"></sup>Cherethites and the Pelethites, and David's sons were priests."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>And David said, “Is there still anyone left of the house of Saul, that I may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8229A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8229A\"></sup>show him kindness for Jonathan's sake?”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now there was a servant of the house of Saul whose name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8230B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8230B\"></sup>Ziba, and they called him to David. And the king said to him, “Are you Ziba?” And he said, “I am your servant.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And the king said, “Is there not still someone of the house of Saul, that I may show <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8231C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8231C\"></sup>the kindness of God to him?” Ziba said to the king, “There is still a son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8231D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8231D\"></sup>Jonathan; he is crippled in his feet.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king said to him, “Where is he?” And Ziba said to the king, “He is in the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8232E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8232E\"></sup>Machir the son of Ammiel, at Lo-debar.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then King David sent and brought him from the house of Machir the son of Ammiel, at Lo-debar.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8234F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8234F\"></sup>Mephibosheth the son of Jonathan, son of Saul, came to David and fell on his face and paid homage. And David said, “Mephibosheth!” And he answered, “Behold, I am your servant.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And David said to him, “Do not fear, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8235G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8235G\"></sup>for I will show you kindness for the sake of your father Jonathan, and I will restore to you all the land of Saul your father, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8235H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8235H\"></sup>you shall eat at my table always.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he paid homage and said, “What is your servant, that you should show regard for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8236I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8236I\"></sup>a dead dog such as I?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the king called Ziba, Saul's servant, and said to him, “All that belonged to Saul and to all his house I have given to your master's grandson.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And you and your sons and your servants shall till the land for him and shall bring in the produce, that your master's grandson may have bread to eat. But Mephibosheth your master's grandson <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8238J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8238J\"></sup>shall always eat at my table.” Now Ziba had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8238K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8238K\"></sup>fifteen sons and twenty servants.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Ziba said to the king, “According to all that my lord the king commands his servant, so will your servant do.” So Mephibosheth <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8239L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8239L\"></sup>ate at David's table, like one of the king's sons.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Mephibosheth had a young son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8240M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8240M\"></sup>whose name was Mica. And all who lived in Ziba's house became Mephibosheth's servants.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Mephibosheth lived in Jerusalem, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8241N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8241N\"></sup>he ate always at the king's table. Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8241O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8241O\"></sup>he was lame in both his feet."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8242A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8242A\"></sup>After this the king of the Ammonites died, and Hanun his son reigned in his place.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And David said, “I will deal loyally with Hanun the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8243B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8243B\"></sup>Nahash, as his father dealt loyally with me.” So David sent by his servants to console him concerning his father. And David's servants came into the land of the Ammonites.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But the princes of the Ammonites said to Hanun their lord, “Do you think, because David has sent comforters to you, that he is honoring your father? Has not David sent his servants to you to search the city and to spy it out and to overthrow it?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Hanun took David's servants and shaved off half the beard of each and cut off their garments in the middle, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8245C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8245C\"></sup>at their hips, and sent them away.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When it was told David, he sent to meet them, for the men were greatly ashamed. And the king said, “Remain at Jericho until your beards have grown and then return.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When the Ammonites saw that they had become a stench to David, the Ammonites sent and hired the Syrians of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8247D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8247D\"></sup>Beth-rehob, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8247E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8247E\"></sup>the Syrians of Zobah, 20,000 foot soldiers, and the king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8247F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8247F\"></sup>Maacah with 1,000 men, and the men of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8247G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8247G\"></sup>Tob, 12,000 men.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And when David heard of it, he sent Joab and all the host of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8248H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8248H\"></sup>the mighty men.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the Ammonites came out and drew up in battle array at the entrance of the gate, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8249I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8249I\"></sup>the Syrians of Zobah and of Rehob and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8249J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8249J\"></sup>the men of Tob and Maacah were by themselves in the open country.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When Joab saw that the battle was set against him both in front and in the rear, he chose some of the best men of Israel and arrayed them against the Syrians.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The rest of his men he put in the charge of Abishai his brother, and he arrayed them against the Ammonites.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And he said, “If the Syrians are too strong for me, then you shall help me, but if the Ammonites are too strong for you, then I will come and help you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8253K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8253K\"></sup>Be of good courage, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8253L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8253L\"></sup>let us be courageous for our people, and for the cities of our God, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8253M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8253M\"></sup>may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> do what seems good to him.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Joab and the people who were with him drew near to battle against the Syrians, and they fled before him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And when the Ammonites saw that the Syrians fled, they likewise fled before Abishai and entered the city. Then Joab returned from fighting against the Ammonites and came to Jerusalem.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But when the Syrians saw that they had been defeated by Israel, they gathered themselves together.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Hadadezer sent and brought out the Syrians who were beyond <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8257N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8257N\"></sup>the Euphrates. They came to Helam, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8257O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8257O\"></sup>Shobach the commander of the army of Hadadezer at their head.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And when it was told David, he gathered all Israel together and crossed the Jordan and came to Helam. The Syrians arrayed themselves against David and fought with him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the Syrians fled before Israel, and David killed of the Syrians the men of 700 chariots, and 40,000 horsemen, and wounded <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8259P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8259P\"></sup>Shobach the commander of their army, so that he died there.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And when all the kings who were servants of Hadadezer saw that they had been defeated by Israel, they made peace with Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8260Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8260Q\"></sup>and became subject to them. So the Syrians were afraid to save the Ammonites anymore."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8261A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8261A\"></sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8261B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8261B\"></sup>In the spring of the year, the time when kings go out to battle, David sent Joab, and his servants with him, and all Israel. And they ravaged the Ammonites and besieged <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8261C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8261C\"></sup>Rabbah. But David remained at Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It happened, late one afternoon, when David arose from his couch and was walking on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8262D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8262D\"></sup>the roof of the king's house, that he saw from the roof a woman bathing; and the woman was very beautiful.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And David sent and inquired about the woman. And one said, “Is not this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8263E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8263E\"></sup>Bathsheba, the daughter of Eliam, the wife of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8263F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8263F\"></sup>Uriah the Hittite?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So David sent messengers and took her, and she came to him, and he lay with her. (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8264G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8264G\"></sup>Now she had been purifying herself from her uncleanness.) Then she returned to her house.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the woman conceived, and she sent and told David, “I am pregnant.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So David sent word to Joab, “Send me Uriah the Hittite.” And Joab sent Uriah to David.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When Uriah came to him, David asked how Joab was doing and how the people were doing and how the war was going.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then David said to Uriah, “Go down to your house and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8268H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8268H\"></sup>wash your feet.” And Uriah went out of the king's house, and there followed him a present from the king.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Uriah slept at the door of the king's house with all the servants of his lord, and did not go down to his house.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When they told David, “Uriah did not go down to his house,” David said to Uriah, “Have you not come from a journey? Why did you not go down to your house?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Uriah said to David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8271I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8271I\"></sup>“The ark and Israel and Judah dwell in booths, and my lord Joab and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8271J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8271J\"></sup>the servants of my lord are camping in the open field. Shall I then go to my house, to eat and to drink and to lie with my wife? As you live, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8271K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8271K\"></sup>as your soul lives, I will not do this thing.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then David said to Uriah, “Remain here today also, and tomorrow I will send you back.” So Uriah remained in Jerusalem that day and the next.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And David invited him, and he ate in his presence and drank, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8273L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8273L\"></sup>so that he made him drunk. And in the evening he went out to lie on his couch with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8273M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8273M\"></sup>the servants of his lord, but he did not go down to his house.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In the morning David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8274N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8274N\"></sup>wrote a letter to Joab and sent it by the hand of Uriah.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>In the letter he wrote, “Set Uriah in the forefront of the hardest fighting, and then draw back from him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8275O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8275O\"></sup>that he may be struck down, and die.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And as Joab was besieging the city, he assigned Uriah to the place where he knew there were valiant men.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the men of the city came out and fought with Joab, and some of the servants of David among the people fell. Uriah the Hittite also died.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Joab sent and told David all the news about the fighting.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And he instructed the messenger, “When you have finished telling all the news about the fighting to the king,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>then, if the king's anger rises, and if he says to you, ‘Why did you go so near the city to fight? Did you not know that they would shoot from the wall?",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8281P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8281P\"></sup>Who killed Abimelech the son of Jerubbesheth? Did not a woman cast an upper millstone on him from the wall, so that he died at Thebez? Why did you go so near the wall?’ then you shall say, ‘Your servant Uriah the Hittite is dead also.’”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So the messenger went and came and told David all that Joab had sent him to tell.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The messenger said to David, “The men gained an advantage over us and came out against us in the field, but we drove them back to the entrance of the gate.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the archers shot at your servants from the wall. Some of the king's servants are dead, and your servant Uriah the Hittite is dead also.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>David said to the messenger, “Thus shall you say to Joab, ‘Do not let this matter displease you, for the sword devours now one and now another. Strengthen your attack against the city and overthrow it.’ And encourage him.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When the wife of Uriah heard that Uriah her husband was dead, she lamented over her husband.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And when the mourning was over, David sent and brought her to his house, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8287Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8287Q\"></sup>she became his wife and bore him a son. But the thing that David had done displeased the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8288A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8288A\"></sup>Nathan to David. He came to him and said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8288B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8288B\"></sup>“There were two men in a certain city, the one rich and the other poor.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The rich man had very many flocks and herds,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>but the poor man had nothing but one little ewe lamb, which he had bought. And he brought it up, and it grew up with him and with his children. It used to eat of his morsel and drink from his cup and lie in his arms, and it was like a daughter to him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now there came a traveler to the rich man, and he was unwilling to take one of his own flock or herd to prepare for the guest who had come to him, but he took the poor man's lamb and prepared it for the man who had come to him.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then David's anger was greatly kindled against the man, and he said to Nathan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8292C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8292C\"></sup>“As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, the man who has done this deserves to die,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and he shall restore the lamb <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8293D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8293D\"></sup>fourfold, because he did this thing, and because he had no pity.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Nathan said to David, “You are the man! Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8294E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8294E\"></sup>‘I anointed you king over Israel, and I delivered you out of the hand of Saul.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And I gave you your master's house and your master's wives into your arms and gave you the house of Israel and of Judah. And if this were too little, I would add to you as much more.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8296F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8296F\"></sup>Why have you despised the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8296G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8296G\"></sup>to do what is evil in his sight? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8296H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8296H\"></sup>You have struck down Uriah the Hittite with the sword and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8296I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8296I\"></sup>have taken his wife to be your wife and have killed him with the sword of the Ammonites.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now therefore the sword shall never depart from your house, because you have despised me and have taken the wife of Uriah the Hittite to be your wife.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Behold, I will raise up evil against you out of your own house. And I will take your wives before your eyes and give them to your neighbor, and he shall lie with your wives in the sight of this sun.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For you did it secretly, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8299J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8299J\"></sup>but I will do this thing before all Israel and before the sun.’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8300K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8300K\"></sup>David said to Nathan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8300L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8300L\"></sup>“I have sinned against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And Nathan said to David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8300M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8300M\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> also has put away your sin; you shall not die.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Nevertheless, because by this deed you have utterly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8301N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8301N\"></sup>scorned the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the child who is born to you shall die.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Nathan went to his house.And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> afflicted the child that Uriah's wife bore to David, and he became sick.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>David therefore sought God on behalf of the child. And David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8303O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8303O\"></sup>fasted and went in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8303P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8303P\"></sup>and lay all night on the ground.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the elders of his house stood beside him, to raise him from the ground, but he would not, nor did he eat food with them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>On the seventh day the child died. And the servants of David were afraid to tell him that the child was dead, for they said, “Behold, while the child was yet alive, we spoke to him, and he did not listen to us. How then can we say to him the child is dead? He may do himself some harm.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But when David saw that his servants were whispering together, David understood that the child was dead. And David said to his servants, “Is the child dead?” They said, “He is dead.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then David arose from the earth <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8307Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8307Q\"></sup>and washed and anointed himself and changed his clothes. And he went into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8307R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8307R\"></sup>and worshiped. He then went to his own house. And when he asked, they set food before him, and he ate.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then his servants said to him, “What is this thing that you have done? You fasted and wept for the child while he was alive; but when the child died, you arose and ate food.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He said, “While the child was still alive, I fasted and wept, for I said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8309S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8309S\"></sup>‘Who knows whether the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be gracious to me, that the child may live?’",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But now he is dead. Why should I fast? Can I bring him back again? I shall go to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8310T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8310T\"></sup>but he will not return to me.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then David comforted his wife, Bathsheba, and went in to her and lay with her, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8311U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8311U\"></sup>she bore a son, and he called his name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8311V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8311V\"></sup>Solomon. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> loved him",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and sent a message by Nathan the prophet. So he called his name Jedidiah, because of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8313W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8313W\"></sup>Now Joab <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8313X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8313X\"></sup>fought against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8313Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8313Y\"></sup>Rabbah of the Ammonites and took the royal city.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And Joab sent messengers to David and said, “I have fought against Rabbah; moreover, I have taken the city of waters.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now then gather the rest of the people together and encamp against the city and take it, lest I take the city and it be called by my name.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So David gathered all the people together and went to Rabbah and fought against it and took it.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And he took the crown of their king from his head. The weight of it was a talent of gold, and in it was a precious stone, and it was placed on David's head. And he brought out the spoil of the city, a very great amount.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And he brought out the people who were in it and set them to labor with saws and iron picks and iron axes and made them toil at the brick kilns. And thus he did to all the cities of the Ammonites. Then David and all the people returned to Jerusalem."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8319A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8319A\"></sup>Absalom, David's son, had a beautiful sister, whose name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8319B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8319B\"></sup>Tamar. And after a time Amnon, David's son, loved her.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Amnon was so tormented that he made himself ill because of his sister Tamar, for she was a virgin, and it seemed impossible to Amnon to do anything to her.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Amnon had a friend, whose name was Jonadab, the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8321C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8321C\"></sup>Shimeah, David's brother. And Jonadab was a very crafty man.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he said to him, “O son of the king, why are you so haggard morning after morning? Will you not tell me?” Amnon said to him, “I love Tamar, my brother Absalom's sister.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Jonadab said to him, “Lie down on your bed and pretend to be ill. And when your father comes to see you, say to him, ‘Let my sister Tamar come and give me bread to eat, and prepare the food in my sight, that I may see it and eat it from her hand.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Amnon lay down and pretended to be ill. And when the king came to see him, Amnon said to the king, “Please let my sister Tamar come and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8324D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8324D\"></sup>make a couple of cakes in my sight, that I may eat from her hand.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then David sent home to Tamar, saying, “Go to your brother Amnon's house and prepare food for him.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Tamar went to her brother Amnon's house, where he was lying down. And she took dough and kneaded it and made cakes in his sight and baked the cakes.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And she took the pan and emptied it out before him, but he refused to eat. And Amnon said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8327E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8327E\"></sup>“Send out everyone from me.” So everyone went out from him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Amnon said to Tamar, “Bring the food into the chamber, that I may eat from your hand.” And Tamar took the cakes she had made and brought them into the chamber to Amnon her brother.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But when she brought them near him to eat, he took hold of her and said to her, “Come, lie with me, my sister.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>She answered him, “No, my brother, do not violate me, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8330F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8330F\"></sup>such a thing is not done in Israel; do not do this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8330G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8330G\"></sup>outrageous thing.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>As for me, where could I carry my shame? And as for you, you would be as one of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8331H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8331H\"></sup>the outrageous fools in Israel. Now therefore, please speak to the king, for he will not withhold me from you.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But he would not listen to her, and being stronger than she, he violated her and lay with her.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Amnon hated her with very great hatred, so that the hatred with which he hated her was greater than the love with which he had loved her. And Amnon said to her, “Get up! Go!”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But she said to him, “No, my brother, for this wrong in sending me away is greater than the other that you did to me.” But he would not listen to her.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He called the young man who served him and said, “Put this woman out of my presence and bolt the door after her.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now she was wearing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8336I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8336I\"></sup>a long robe with sleeves, for thus were the virgin daughters of the king dressed. So his servant put her out and bolted the door after her.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And Tamar <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8337J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8337J\"></sup>put ashes on her head and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8337K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8337K\"></sup>tore the long robe that she wore. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8337L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8337L\"></sup>she laid her hand on her head and went away, crying aloud as she went.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And her brother Absalom said to her, “Has Amnon your brother been with you? Now hold your peace, my sister. He is your brother; do not take this to heart.” So Tamar lived, a desolate woman, in her brother Absalom's house.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When King David heard of all these things, he was very angry.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But Absalom spoke to Amnon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8340M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8340M\"></sup>neither good nor bad, for Absalom hated Amnon, because he had violated his sister Tamar.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>After two full years Absalom had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8341N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8341N\"></sup>sheepshearers at Baal-hazor, which is near Ephraim, and Absalom invited all the king's sons.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Absalom came to the king and said, “Behold, your servant has sheepshearers. Please let the king and his servants go with your servant.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But the king said to Absalom, “No, my son, let us not all go, lest we be burdensome to you.” He pressed him, but he would not go but gave him his blessing.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then Absalom said, “If not, please let my brother Amnon go with us.” And the king said to him, “Why should he go with you?”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But Absalom pressed him until he let Amnon and all the king's sons go with him.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Absalom commanded his servants, “Mark when Amnon's <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8346O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8346O\"></sup>heart is merry with wine, and when I say to you, ‘Strike Amnon,’ then kill him. Do not fear; have I not commanded you? Be courageous and be valiant.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So the servants of Absalom did to Amnon as Absalom had commanded. Then all the king's sons arose, and each mounted his mule and fled.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>While they were on the way, news came to David, “Absalom has struck down all the king's sons, and not one of them is left.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then the king arose and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8349P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8349P\"></sup>tore his garments and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8349Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8349Q\"></sup>lay on the earth. And all his servants who were standing by tore their garments.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8350R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8350R\"></sup>Jonadab the son of Shimeah, David's brother, said, “Let not my lord suppose that they have killed all the young men, the king's sons, for Amnon alone is dead. For by the command of Absalom this has been determined from the day he violated his sister Tamar.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Now therefore let not my lord the king so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8351S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8351S\"></sup>take it to heart as to suppose that all the king's sons are dead, for Amnon alone is dead.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8352T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8352T\"></sup>But Absalom fled. And the young man who kept the watch lifted up his eyes and looked, and behold, many people were coming from the road behind him by the side of the mountain.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And Jonadab said to the king, “Behold, the king's sons have come; as your servant said, so it has come about.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And as soon as he had finished speaking, behold, the king's sons came and lifted up their voice and wept. And the king also and all his servants wept very bitterly.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8355U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8355U\"></sup>But Absalom fled and went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8355V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8355V\"></sup>Talmai the son of Ammihud, king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8355W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8355W\"></sup>Geshur. And David mourned for his son day after day.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8356X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8356X\"></sup>So Absalom fled and went to Geshur, and was there three years.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And the spirit of the king longed to go out to Absalom, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8357Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8357Y\"></sup>he was comforted about Amnon, since he was dead."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>Now Joab the son of Zeruiah knew <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8358A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8358A\"></sup>that the king's heart went out to Absalom.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Joab sent to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8359B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8359B\"></sup>Tekoa and brought from there a wise woman and said to her, “Pretend to be a mourner and put on mourning garments. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8359C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8359C\"></sup>Do not anoint yourself with oil, but behave like a woman who has been mourning many days for the dead.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Go to the king and speak thus to him.” So Joab <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8360D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8360D\"></sup>put the words in her mouth.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When the woman of Tekoa came to the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8361E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8361E\"></sup>she fell on her face to the ground and paid homage and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8361F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8361F\"></sup>“Save me, O king.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the king said to her, “What is your trouble?” She answered, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8362G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8362G\"></sup>“Alas, I am a widow; my husband is dead.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And your servant had two sons, and they quarreled with one another in the field. There was no one to separate them, and one struck the other and killed him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And now the whole clan has risen against your servant, and they say, ‘Give up the man who struck his brother, that we may put him to death for the life of his brother whom he killed.’ And so they would <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8364H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8364H\"></sup>destroy the heir also. Thus they would quench my coal that is left and leave to my husband neither name nor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8364I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8364I\"></sup>remnant on the face of the earth.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the king said to the woman, “Go to your house, and I will give orders concerning you.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the woman of Tekoa said to the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8366J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8366J\"></sup>“On me be the guilt, my lord the king, and on my father's house; let the king and his throne be guiltless.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The king said, “If anyone says anything to you, bring him to me, and he shall never touch you again.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then she said, “Please let the king invoke the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8368K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8368K\"></sup>the avenger of blood kill no more, and my son be not destroyed.” He said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8368L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8368L\"></sup>“As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8368M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8368M\"></sup>not one hair of your son shall fall to the ground.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the woman said, “Please let your servant speak a word to my lord the king.” He said, “Speak.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the woman said, “Why then have you planned such a thing against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8370N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8370N\"></sup>the people of God? For in giving this decision the king convicts himself, inasmuch as the king does not bring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8370O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8370O\"></sup>his banished one home again.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>We must all die; we are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8371P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8371P\"></sup>like water spilled on the ground, which cannot be gathered up again. But God will not take away life, and he devises means <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8371Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8371Q\"></sup>so that the banished one will not remain an outcast.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now I have come to say this to my lord the king because the people have made me afraid, and your servant thought, ‘I will speak to the king; it may be that the king will perform the request of his servant.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For the king will hear and deliver his servant from the hand of the man who would destroy me and my son together from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8373R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8373R\"></sup>the heritage of God.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And your servant thought, ‘The word of my lord the king will set me at rest,’ for my lord the king is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8374S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8374S\"></sup>like the angel of God to discern good and evil. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God be with you!”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the king answered the woman, “Do not hide from me anything I ask you.” And the woman said, “Let my lord the king speak.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The king said, “Is the hand of Joab with you in all this?” The woman answered and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8376T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8376T\"></sup>“As surely as you live, my lord the king, one cannot turn to the right hand or to the left from anything that my lord the king has said. It was your servant Joab who commanded me; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8376U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8376U\"></sup>it was he who put all these words in the mouth of your servant.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>In order to change the course of things your servant Joab did this. But my lord has wisdom like the wisdom of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8377V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8377V\"></sup>the angel of God to know all things that are on the earth.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the king said to Joab, “Behold now, I grant this; go, bring back the young man Absalom.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Joab fell on his face to the ground and paid homage <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8379W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8379W\"></sup>and blessed the king. And Joab said, “Today your servant knows that I have found favor in your sight, my lord the king, in that the king has granted the request of his servant.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So Joab arose and went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8380X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8380X\"></sup>Geshur and brought Absalom to Jerusalem.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the king said, “Let him dwell apart in his own house; he is not to come into my presence.” So Absalom lived apart in his own house and did not come into the king's presence.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now in all Israel there was no one so much to be praised for his handsome appearance as Absalom. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8382Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8382Y\"></sup>From the sole of his foot to the crown of his head there was no blemish in him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And when he cut the hair of his head (for at the end of every year he used to cut it; when it was heavy on him, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8383Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8383Z\"></sup>cut it), he weighed the hair of his head, two hundred shekels by the king's weight.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>There were born <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8384AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8384AA\"></sup>to Absalom three sons, and one daughter whose name was Tamar. She was a beautiful woman.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Absalom lived two full years in Jerusalem, without coming into the king's presence.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Absalom sent for Joab, to send him to the king, but Joab would not come to him. And he sent a second time, but Joab would not come.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then he said to his servants, “See, Joab's field is next to mine, and he has barley there; go and set it on fire.” So Absalom's servants set the field on fire.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Joab arose and went to Absalom at his house and said to him, “Why have your servants set my field on fire?”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Absalom answered Joab, “Behold, I sent word to you, ‘Come here, that I may send you to the king, to ask, “Why have I come from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8389AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8389AB\"></sup>Geshur? It would be better for me to be there still.” Now therefore let me go into the presence of the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8389AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8389AC\"></sup>and if there is guilt in me, let him put me to death.’”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then Joab went to the king and told him, and he summoned Absalom. So he came to the king and bowed himself on his face to the ground before the king, and the king kissed Absalom."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>After this Absalom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8391A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8391A\"></sup>got himself a chariot and horses, and fifty men to run before him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Absalom used to rise early and stand beside <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8392B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8392B\"></sup>the way of the gate. And when any man had a dispute to come before the king for judgment, Absalom would call to him and say, “From what city are you?” And when he said, “Your servant is of such and such a tribe in Israel,”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Absalom would say to him, “See, your claims are good and right, but there is no man designated by the king to hear you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Absalom would say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8394C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8394C\"></sup>“Oh that I were judge in the land! Then every man with a dispute or cause might come to me, and I would give him justice.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And whenever a man came near to pay homage to him, he would put out his hand and take hold of him and kiss him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Thus Absalom did to all of Israel who came to the king for judgment. So Absalom stole the hearts of the men of Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And at the end of four years Absalom said to the king, “Please let me go and pay my vow, which I have vowed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in Hebron.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For your servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8398D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8398D\"></sup>vowed a vow <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8398E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8398E\"></sup>while I lived at Geshur in Aram, saying, ‘If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will indeed bring me back to Jerusalem, then I will offer worship to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The king said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8399F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8399F\"></sup>“Go in peace.” So he arose and went to Hebron.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But Absalom sent secret messengers throughout all the tribes of Israel, saying, “As soon as you hear the sound of the trumpet, then say, ‘Absalom is king at Hebron!’”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>With Absalom went two hundred men from Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8401G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8401G\"></sup>who were invited guests, and they went in their innocence and knew nothing.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And while Absalom was offering the sacrifices, he sent for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8402H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8402H\"></sup>Ahithophel the Gilonite, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8402I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8402I\"></sup>David's counselor, from his city <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8402J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8402J\"></sup>Giloh. And the conspiracy grew strong, and the people with Absalom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8402K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8402K\"></sup>kept increasing.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And a messenger came to David, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8403L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8403L\"></sup>“The hearts of the men of Israel have gone after Absalom.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then David said to all his servants who were with him at Jerusalem, “Arise, and let us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8404M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8404M\"></sup>flee, or else there will be no escape for us from Absalom. Go quickly, lest he overtake us quickly and bring down ruin on us and strike the city with the edge of the sword.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the king's servants said to the king, “Behold, your servants are ready to do whatever my lord the king decides.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So the king went out, and all his household after him. And the king left <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8406N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8406N\"></sup>ten concubines to keep the house.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the king went out, and all the people after him. And they halted at the last house.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8408O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8408O\"></sup>all his servants passed by him, and all the Cherethites, and all the Pelethites, and all the six hundred Gittites who had followed him from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8408P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8408P\"></sup>Gath, passed on before the king.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the king said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8409Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8409Q\"></sup>Ittai the Gittite, “Why do you also go with us? Go back and stay with the king, for you are a foreigner and also an exile from your home.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You came only yesterday, and shall I today make you wander about with us, since I go <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8410R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8410R\"></sup>I know not where? Go back and take your brothers with you, and may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> show steadfast love and faithfulness to you.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But Ittai answered the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8411S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8411S\"></sup>“As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, and as my lord the king lives, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8411T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8411T\"></sup>wherever my lord the king shall be, whether for death or for life, there also will your servant be.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And David said to Ittai, “Go then, pass on.” So Ittai the Gittite passed on with all his men and all the little ones who were with him.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And all the land wept aloud as all the people passed by, and the king crossed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8413U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8413U\"></sup>the brook <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8413V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8413V\"></sup>Kidron, and all the people passed on toward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8413W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8413W\"></sup>the wilderness.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8414X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8414X\"></sup>Abiathar came up, and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8414Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8414Y\"></sup>Zadok came also with all the Levites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8414Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8414Z\"></sup>bearing the ark of the covenant of God. And they set down the ark of God until the people had all passed out of the city.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then the king said to Zadok, “Carry the ark of God back into the city. If I find favor in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8415AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8415AA\"></sup>bring me back and let me see both it and his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8415AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8415AB\"></sup>dwelling place.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But if he says, ‘I have no <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8416AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8416AC\"></sup>pleasure in you,’ behold, here I am, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8416AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8416AD\"></sup>let him do to me what seems good to him.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The king also said to Zadok the priest, “Are you not a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8417AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8417AE\"></sup>seer? Go back to the city in peace, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8417AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8417AF\"></sup>your two sons, Ahimaaz your son, and Jonathan the son of Abiathar.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>See, I will wait at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8418AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8418AG\"></sup>the fords of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8418AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8418AH\"></sup>the wilderness until word comes from you to inform me.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So Zadok and Abiathar carried the ark of God back to Jerusalem, and they remained there.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But David went up the ascent of the Mount of Olives, weeping as he went, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8420AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8420AI\"></sup>barefoot and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8420AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8420AJ\"></sup>with his head covered. And all the people who were with him covered their heads, and they went up, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8420AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8420AK\"></sup>weeping as they went.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And it was told David, “Ahithophel is among the conspirators with Absalom.” And David said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8421AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8421AL\"></sup>turn the counsel of Ahithophel into foolishness.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>While David was coming to the summit, where God was worshiped, behold, Hushai <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8422AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8422AM\"></sup>the Archite came to meet him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8422AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8422AN\"></sup>with his coat torn and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8422AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8422AO\"></sup>dirt on his head.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>David said to him, “If you go on with me, you will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8423AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8423AP\"></sup>a burden to me.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But if you return to the city and say to Absalom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8424AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8424AQ\"></sup>‘I will be your servant, O king; as I have been your father's servant in time past, so now I will be your servant,’ then you will defeat for me the counsel of Ahithophel.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Are not Zadok and Abiathar the priests with you there? So whatever you hear from the king's house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8425AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8425AR\"></sup>tell it to Zadok and Abiathar the priests.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8426AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8426AS\"></sup>their two sons are with them there, Ahimaaz, Zadok's son, and Jonathan, Abiathar's son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8426AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8426AT\"></sup>and by them you shall send to me everything you hear.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>So Hushai, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8427AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8427AU\"></sup>David's friend, came into the city, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8427AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8427AV\"></sup>just as Absalom was entering Jerusalem."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>When David had passed a little beyond <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8428A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8428A\"></sup>the summit, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8428B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8428B\"></sup>Ziba the servant of Mephibosheth met him, with a couple of donkeys saddled, bearing two hundred loaves of bread, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8428C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8428C\"></sup>a hundred bunches of raisins, a hundred of summer fruits, and a skin of wine.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the king said to Ziba, “Why have you brought these?” Ziba answered, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8429D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8429D\"></sup>“The donkeys are for the king's household to ride on, the bread and summer fruit for the young men to eat, and the wine for those who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8429E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8429E\"></sup>faint in the wilderness to drink.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And the king said, “And where is your master's son?” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8430F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8430F\"></sup>Ziba said to the king, “Behold, he remains in Jerusalem, for he said, ‘Today the house of Israel will give me back the kingdom of my father.’”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the king said to Ziba, “Behold, all that belonged to Mephibosheth is now yours.” And Ziba said, “I pay homage; let me ever find favor in your sight, my lord the king.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When King David came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8432G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8432G\"></sup>Bahurim, there came out a man of the family of the house of Saul, whose name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8432H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8432H\"></sup>Shimei, the son of Gera, and as he came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8432I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8432I\"></sup>he cursed continually.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he threw stones at David and at all the servants of King David, and all the people and all the mighty men were on his right hand and on his left.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Shimei said as he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8434J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8434J\"></sup>cursed, “Get out, get out, you man of blood, you worthless man!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8435K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8435K\"></sup>has avenged on you all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8435L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8435L\"></sup>the blood of the house of Saul, in whose place you have reigned, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given the kingdom into the hand of your son Absalom. See, your evil is on you, for you are a man of blood.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Abishai the son of Zeruiah said to the king, “Why should this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8436M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8436M\"></sup>dead dog <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8436N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8436N\"></sup>curse my lord the king? Let me go over and take off his head.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But the king said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8437O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8437O\"></sup>“What have I to do with you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8437P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8437P\"></sup>you sons of Zeruiah? If he is cursing because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has said to him, ‘Curse David,’ who then shall say, ‘Why have you done so?’”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And David said to Abishai and to all his servants, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8438Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8438Q\"></sup>my own son seeks my life; how much more now may this Benjaminite! Leave him alone, and let him curse, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has told him to.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>It may be that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will look on the wrong done to me, and that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will repay me with good for his cursing today.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So David and his men went on the road, while Shimei went along on the hillside opposite him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8440R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8440R\"></sup>cursed as he went and threw stones at him and flung dust.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And the king, and all the people who were with him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8441S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8441S\"></sup>arrived weary at the Jordan. And there he refreshed himself.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8442T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8442T\"></sup>Now Absalom and all the people, the men of Israel, came to Jerusalem, and Ahithophel with him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And when Hushai the Archite, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8443U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8443U\"></sup>David's friend, came to Absalom, Hushai said to Absalom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8443V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8443V\"></sup>“Long live the king! Long live the king!”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And Absalom said to Hushai, “Is this your loyalty to your friend? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8444W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8444W\"></sup>Why did you not go with your friend?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Hushai said to Absalom, “No, for whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and this people and all the men of Israel have chosen, his I will be, and with him I will remain.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And again, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8446X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8446X\"></sup>whom should I serve? Should it not be his son? As I have served your father, so I will serve you.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Absalom said to Ahithophel, “Give your counsel. What shall we do?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Ahithophel said to Absalom, “Go in to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8448Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8448Y\"></sup>your father's concubines, whom he has left to keep the house, and all Israel will hear that you have made yourself a stench to your father, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8448Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8448Z\"></sup>the hands of all who are with you will be strengthened.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So they pitched a tent for Absalom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8449AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8449AA\"></sup>on the roof. And Absalom went in to his father's concubines <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8449AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8449AB\"></sup>in the sight of all Israel.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now in those days the counsel that Ahithophel gave was as if one consulted the word of God; so was all the counsel of Ahithophel esteemed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8450AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8450AC\"></sup>both by David and by Absalom."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Moreover, Ahithophel said to Absalom, “Let me choose twelve thousand men, and I will arise and pursue David tonight.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I will come upon him while he is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8452A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8452A\"></sup>weary and discouraged and throw him into a panic, and all the people who are with him will flee. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8452B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8452B\"></sup>I will strike down only the king,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and I will bring all the people back to you as a bride comes home to her husband. You seek the life of only one man, and all the people will be at peace.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the advice seemed right in the eyes of Absalom and all the elders of Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Absalom said, “Call <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8455C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8455C\"></sup>Hushai the Archite also, and let us hear what he has to say.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And when Hushai came to Absalom, Absalom said to him, “Thus has Ahithophel spoken; shall we do as he says? If not, you speak.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Hushai said to Absalom, “This time the counsel that Ahithophel has given is not good.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Hushai said, “You know that your father and his men are mighty men, and that they are enraged, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8458D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8458D\"></sup>like a bear robbed of her cubs in the field. Besides, your father is expert in war; he will not spend the night with the people.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Behold, even now he has hidden himself in one of the pits or in some other place. And as soon as some of the people fall at the first attack, whoever hears it will say, ‘There has been a slaughter among the people who follow Absalom.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then even the valiant man, whose heart is like the heart of a lion, will utterly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8460E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8460E\"></sup>melt with fear, for all Israel knows that your father is a mighty man, and that those who are with him are valiant men.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But my counsel is that all Israel be gathered to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8461F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8461F\"></sup>from Dan to Beersheba, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8461G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8461G\"></sup>as the sand by the sea for multitude, and that you go to battle in person.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So we shall come upon him in some place where he is to be found, and we shall light upon him as the dew falls on the ground, and of him and all the men with him not one will be left.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>If he withdraws into a city, then all Israel will bring ropes to that city, and we shall drag it into the valley, until not even a pebble is to be found there.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And Absalom and all the men of Israel said, “The counsel of Hushai the Archite is better than the counsel of Ahithophel.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8464H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8464H\"></sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had ordained to defeat the good counsel of Ahithophel, so that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> might bring harm upon Absalom.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8465I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8465I\"></sup>Then Hushai said to Zadok and Abiathar the priests, “Thus and so did Ahithophel counsel Absalom and the elders of Israel, and thus and so have I counseled.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now therefore send quickly and tell David, ‘Do not stay tonight at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8466J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8466J\"></sup>the fords of the wilderness, but by all means pass over, lest the king and all the people who are with him be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8466K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8466K\"></sup>swallowed up.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8467L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8467L\"></sup>Jonathan and Ahimaaz were waiting at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8467M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8467M\"></sup>En-rogel. A female servant was to go and tell them, and they were to go and tell King David, for they were not to be seen entering the city.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But a young man saw them and told Absalom. So both of them went away quickly and came to the house of a man at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8468N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8468N\"></sup>Bahurim, who had a well in his courtyard. And they went down into it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8469O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8469O\"></sup>And the woman took and spread a covering over the well's mouth and scattered grain on it, and nothing was known of it.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Absalom's servants came to the woman at the house, they said, “Where are Ahimaaz and Jonathan?” And the woman said to them, “They have gone over the brook of water.” And when they had sought and could not find them, they returned to Jerusalem.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>After they had gone, the men came up out of the well, and went and told King David. They said to David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8471P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8471P\"></sup>“Arise, and go quickly over the water, for thus and so has Ahithophel counseled against you.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then David arose, and all the people who were with him, and they crossed the Jordan. By daybreak not one was left who had not crossed the Jordan.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When Ahithophel saw that his counsel was not followed, he saddled his donkey and went off home to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8473Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8473Q\"></sup>his own city. He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8473R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8473R\"></sup>set his house in order and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8473S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8473S\"></sup>hanged himself, and he died and was buried in the tomb of his father.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then David came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8474T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8474T\"></sup>Mahanaim. And Absalom crossed the Jordan with all the men of Israel.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now Absalom had set <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8475U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8475U\"></sup>Amasa over the army instead of Joab. Amasa was the son of a man named Ithra the Ishmaelite, who had married Abigal the daughter of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8475V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8475V\"></sup>Nahash, sister of Zeruiah, Joab's mother.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And Israel and Absalom encamped in the land of Gilead.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When David came to Mahanaim, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8477W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8477W\"></sup>Shobi the son of Nahash from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8477X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8477X\"></sup>Rabbah of the Ammonites, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8477Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8477Y\"></sup>Machir the son of Ammiel from Lo-debar, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8477Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8477Z\"></sup>Barzillai the Gileadite from Rogelim,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>brought beds, basins, and earthen vessels, wheat, barley, flour, parched grain, beans and lentils,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>honey and curds and sheep and cheese from the herd, for David and the people with him to eat, for they said, “The people are hungry and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8479AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8479AA\"></sup>weary and thirsty <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8479AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8479AB\"></sup>in the wilderness.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Then David mustered the men who were with him and set over them commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And David sent out the army, one third under the command of Joab, one third under the command of Abishai the son of Zeruiah, Joab's brother, and one third under the command of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8481A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8481A\"></sup>Ittai the Gittite. And the king said to the men, “I myself will also go out with you.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8482B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8482B\"></sup>But the men said, “You shall not go out. For if we flee, they will not care about us. If half of us die, they will not care about us. But you are worth ten thousand of us. Therefore it is better that you send us help from the city.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king said to them, “Whatever seems best to you I will do.” So the king stood at the side of the gate, while all the army marched out by hundreds and by thousands.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the king ordered Joab and Abishai and Ittai, “Deal gently for my sake with the young man Absalom.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8484C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8484C\"></sup>And all the people heard when the king gave orders to all the commanders about Absalom.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So the army went out into the field against Israel, and the battle was fought in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8485D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8485D\"></sup>forest of Ephraim.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the men of Israel were defeated there by the servants of David, and the loss there was great on that day, twenty thousand men.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The battle spread over the face of all the country, and the forest devoured more people that day than the sword.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Absalom happened to meet the servants of David. Absalom was riding on his mule, and the mule went under the thick branches of a great oak, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8488E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8488E\"></sup>and his head caught fast in the oak, and he was suspended between heaven and earth, while the mule that was under him went on.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And a certain man saw it and told Joab, “Behold, I saw Absalom hanging in an oak.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Joab said to the man who told him, “What, you saw him! Why then did you not strike him there to the ground? I would have been glad to give you ten pieces of silver and a belt.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But the man said to Joab, “Even if I felt in my hand the weight of a thousand pieces of silver, I would not reach out my hand against the king's son, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8491F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8491F\"></sup>in our hearing the king commanded you and Abishai and Ittai, ‘For my sake protect the young man Absalom.’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>On the other hand, if I had dealt treacherously against his life (and there is nothing hidden from the king), then you yourself would have stood aloof.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Joab said, “I will not waste time like this with you.” And he took three javelins in his hand and thrust them into the heart of Absalom while he was still alive in the oak.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And ten young men, Joab's armor-bearers, surrounded Absalom and struck him and killed him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Joab blew the trumpet, and the troops came back from pursuing Israel, for Joab restrained them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And they took Absalom and threw him into a great pit in the forest and raised over him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8496G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8496G\"></sup>a very great heap of stones. And all Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8496H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8496H\"></sup>fled every one to his own home.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now Absalom in his lifetime had taken and set up for himself <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8497I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8497I\"></sup>the pillar that is in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8497J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8497J\"></sup>the King's Valley, for he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8497K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8497K\"></sup>“I have no son to keep my name in remembrance.” He called the pillar after his own name, and it is called Absalom's monument to this day.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Ahimaaz the son of Zadok said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8498L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8498L\"></sup>“Let me run and carry news to the king that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8498M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8498M\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has delivered him from the hand of his enemies.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Joab said to him, “You are not to carry news today. You may carry news another day, but today you shall carry no news, because the king's son is dead.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Joab said to the Cushite, “Go, tell the king what you have seen.” The Cushite bowed before Joab, and ran.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Ahimaaz the son of Zadok said again to Joab, “Come what may, let me also run after the Cushite.” And Joab said, “Why will you run, my son, seeing that you will have no reward for the news?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Come what may,” he said, “I will run.” So he said to him, “Run.” Then Ahimaaz ran by the way of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8502N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8502N\"></sup>the plain, and outran the Cushite.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8503O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8503O\"></sup>was sitting between the two gates, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8503P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8503P\"></sup>the watchman went up to the roof of the gate by the wall, and when he lifted up his eyes and looked, he saw a man running alone.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The watchman called out and told the king. And the king said, “If he is alone, there is news in his mouth.” And he drew nearer and nearer.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The watchman saw another man running. And the watchman called to the gate and said, “See, another man running alone!” The king said, “He also brings news.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The watchman said, “I think the running of the first is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8506Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8506Q\"></sup>like the running of Ahimaaz the son of Zadok.” And the king said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8506R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8506R\"></sup>“He is a good man and comes with good news.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Ahimaaz cried out to the king, “All is well.” And he bowed before the king with his face to the earth and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8507S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8507S\"></sup>“Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who has delivered up the men who raised their hand against my lord the king.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And the king said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8508T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8508T\"></sup>“Is it well with the young man Absalom?” Ahimaaz answered, “When Joab sent the king's servant, your servant, I saw a great commotion, but I do not know what it was.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And the king said, “Turn aside and stand here.” So he turned aside and stood still.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And behold, the Cushite came, and the Cushite said, “Good news for my lord the king! For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8510U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8510U\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has delivered you this day from the hand of all who rose up against you.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The king said to the Cushite, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8511V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8511V\"></sup>“Is it well with the young man Absalom?” And the Cushite answered, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8511W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8511W\"></sup>“May the enemies of my lord the king and all who rise up against you for evil be like that young man.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup> And the king was deeply moved and went up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8512X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8512X\"></sup>to the chamber over the gate and wept. And as he went, he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8512Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8512Y\"></sup>“O my son Absalom, my son, my son Absalom! Would I had died instead of you, O Absalom, my son, my son!”"
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>It was told Joab, “Behold, the king is weeping and mourning for Absalom.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the victory that day was turned into mourning for all the people, for the people heard that day, “The king is grieving for his son.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And the people stole into the city that day as people steal in who are ashamed when they flee in battle.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8516A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8516A\"></sup>covered his face, and the king cried with a loud voice, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8516B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8516B\"></sup>“O my son Absalom, O Absalom, my son, my son!”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Joab came into the house to the king and said, “You have today covered with shame the faces of all your servants, who have this day saved your life and the lives of your sons and your daughters and the lives of your wives and your concubines,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>because you love those who hate you and hate those who love you. For you have made it clear today that commanders and servants are nothing to you, for today I know that if Absalom were alive and all of us were dead today, then you would be pleased.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now therefore arise, go out and speak <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8519C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8519C\"></sup>kindly to your servants, for I swear by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, if you do not go, not a man will stay with you this night, and this will be worse for you than all the evil that has come upon you from your youth until now.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the king arose and took his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8520D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8520D\"></sup>seat in the gate. And the people were all told, “Behold, the king is sitting in the gate.” And all the people came before the king.Now Israel had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8520E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8520E\"></sup>fled every man to his own home.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And all the people were arguing throughout all the tribes of Israel, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8521F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8521F\"></sup>“The king delivered us from the hand of our enemies and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8521G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8521G\"></sup>saved us from the hand of the Philistines, and now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8521H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8521H\"></sup>he has fled out of the land from Absalom.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But Absalom, whom we anointed over us, is dead in battle. Now therefore why do you say nothing about bringing the king back?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And King David sent this message to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8523I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8523I\"></sup>Zadok and Abiathar the priests: “Say to the elders of Judah, ‘Why should you be the last to bring the king back to his house, when the word of all Israel has come to the king?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You are my brothers; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8524J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8524J\"></sup>you are my bone and my flesh. Why then should you be the last to bring back the king?’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And say to Amasa, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8525K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8525K\"></sup>‘Are you not my bone and my flesh? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8525L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8525L\"></sup>God do so to me and more also, if you are not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8525M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8525M\"></sup>commander of my army from now on in place of Joab.’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And he swayed the heart of all the men of Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8526N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8526N\"></sup>as one man, so that they sent word to the king, “Return, both you and all your servants.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So the king came back to the Jordan, and Judah came to Gilgal to meet the king and to bring the king over the Jordan.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8528O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8528O\"></sup>Shimei the son of Gera, the Benjaminite, from Bahurim, hurried to come down with the men of Judah to meet King David.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And with him were a thousand men from Benjamin. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8529P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8529P\"></sup>Ziba the servant of the house of Saul, with his fifteen sons and his twenty servants, rushed down to the Jordan before the king,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and they crossed the ford to bring over the king's household and to do his pleasure. And Shimei the son of Gera fell down before the king, as he was about to cross the Jordan,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and said to the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8531Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8531Q\"></sup>“Let not my lord hold me guilty or remember how your servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8531R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8531R\"></sup>did wrong on the day my lord the king left Jerusalem. Do not let the king take it to heart.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>For your servant knows that I have sinned. Therefore, behold, I have come this day, the first <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8532S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8532S\"></sup>of all the house of Joseph to come down to meet my lord the king.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Abishai the son of Zeruiah answered, “Shall not Shimei be put to death for this, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8533T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8533T\"></sup>he cursed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s anointed?”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But David said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8534U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8534U\"></sup>“What have I to do with you, you sons of Zeruiah, that you should this day be as an adversary to me? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8534V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8534V\"></sup>Shall anyone be put to death in Israel this day? For do I not know that I am this day king over Israel?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8535W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8535W\"></sup>And the king said to Shimei, “You shall not die.” And the king gave him his oath.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8536X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8536X\"></sup>Mephibosheth the son of Saul came down to meet the king. He had neither taken care of his feet nor trimmed his beard nor washed his clothes, from the day the king departed until the day he came back in safety.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And when he came to Jerusalem to meet the king, the king said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8537Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8537Y\"></sup>“Why did you not go with me, Mephibosheth?”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He answered, “My lord, O king, my servant deceived me, for your servant said to him, ‘I will saddle a donkey for myself, that I may ride on it and go with the king.’ For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8538Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8538Z\"></sup>your servant is lame.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8539AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8539AA\"></sup>He has slandered your servant to my lord the king. But my lord the king is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8539AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8539AB\"></sup>like the angel of God; do therefore what seems good to you.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>For all my father's house were but men doomed to death before my lord the king, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8540AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8540AC\"></sup>you set your servant among those who eat at your table. What further right have I, then, to cry to the king?”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And the king said to him, “Why speak any more of your affairs? I have decided: you and Ziba shall divide the land.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And Mephibosheth said to the king, “Oh, let him take it all, since my lord the king has come safely home.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8543AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8543AD\"></sup>Barzillai the Gileadite had come down from Rogelim, and he went on with the king to the Jordan, to escort him over the Jordan.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Barzillai was a very aged man, eighty years old. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8544AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8544AE\"></sup>He had provided the king with food while he stayed at Mahanaim, for he was a very wealthy man.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And the king said to Barzillai, “Come over with me, and I will provide for you with me in Jerusalem.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But Barzillai said to the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8546AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8546AF\"></sup>“How many years have I still to live, that I should go up with the king to Jerusalem?",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>I am this day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8547AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8547AG\"></sup>eighty years old. Can I discern what is pleasant and what is not? Can your servant taste what he eats or what he drinks? Can I still listen to the voice of singing men and singing women? Why then should your servant be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8547AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8547AH\"></sup>an added burden to my lord the king?",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Your servant will go a little way over the Jordan with the king. Why should the king repay me with such a reward?",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Please let your servant return, that I may die in my own city near the grave of my father and my mother. But here is your servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8549AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8549AI\"></sup>Chimham. Let him go over with my lord the king, and do for him whatever seems good to you.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And the king answered, “Chimham shall go over with me, and I will do for him whatever seems good to you, and all that you desire of me I will do for you.”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Then all the people went over the Jordan, and the king went over. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8551AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8551AJ\"></sup>the king kissed Barzillai and blessed him, and he returned to his own home.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The king went on to Gilgal, and Chimham went on with him. All the people of Judah, and also half the people of Israel, brought the king on his way.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Then all the men of Israel came to the king and said to the king, “Why have our brothers the men of Judah stolen you away and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8553AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8553AK\"></sup>brought the king and his household over the Jordan, and all David's men with him?”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>All the men of Judah answered the men of Israel, “Because the king is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8554AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8554AL\"></sup>our close relative. Why then are you angry over this matter? Have we eaten at all at the king's expense? Or has he given us any gift?”",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And the men of Israel answered the men of Judah, “We have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8555AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8555AM\"></sup>ten shares in the king, and in David also we have more than you. Why then did you despise us? Were we not the first to speak of bringing back our king?” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8555AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8555AN\"></sup>But the words of the men of Judah were fiercer than the words of the men of Israel."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Now there happened to be there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8556A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8556A\"></sup>a worthless man, whose name was Sheba, the son of Bichri, a Benjaminite. And he blew the trumpet and said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8556B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8556B\"></sup>“We have no portion in David,and we have no inheritance in the son of Jesse;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8556C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8556C\"></sup>every man to his tents, O Israel!”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So all the men of Israel withdrew from David and followed Sheba the son of Bichri. But the men of Judah followed their king steadfastly from the Jordan to Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And David came to his house at Jerusalem. And the king took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8558D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8558D\"></sup>the ten concubines whom he had left to care for the house and put them in a house under guard and provided for them, but did not go in to them. So they were shut up until the day of their death, living as if in widowhood.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the king said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8559E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8559E\"></sup>Amasa, “Call the men of Judah together to me within three days, and be here yourself.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So Amasa went to summon Judah, but he delayed beyond the set time that had been appointed him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And David said to Abishai, “Now Sheba the son of Bichri will do us more harm than Absalom. Take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8561F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8561F\"></sup>your lord's servants and pursue him, lest he get himself to fortified cities and escape from us.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And there went out after him Joab's men and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8562G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8562G\"></sup>Cherethites and the Pelethites, and all the mighty men. They went out from Jerusalem to pursue Sheba the son of Bichri.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When they were at the great stone that is in Gibeon, Amasa came to meet them. Now Joab was wearing a soldier's garment, and over it was a belt with a sword in its sheath fastened on his thigh, and as he went forward it fell out.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Joab said to Amasa, “Is it well with you, my brother?” And Joab took Amasa by the beard with his right hand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8564H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8564H\"></sup>to kiss him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But Amasa did not observe the sword that was in Joab's hand. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8565I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8565I\"></sup>So Joab struck him with it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8565J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8565J\"></sup>in the stomach and spilled his entrails to the ground without striking a second blow, and he died.Then Joab and Abishai his brother pursued Sheba the son of Bichri.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And one of Joab's young men took his stand by Amasa and said, “Whoever favors Joab, and whoever is for David, let him follow Joab.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Amasa lay wallowing in his blood in the highway. And anyone who came by, seeing him, stopped. And when the man saw that all the people stopped, he carried Amasa out of the highway into the field and threw a garment over him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When he was taken out of the highway, all the people went on after Joab to pursue Sheba the son of Bichri.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And Sheba passed through all the tribes of Israel to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8569K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8569K\"></sup>Abel of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8569L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8569L\"></sup>Beth-maacah, and all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8569M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8569M\"></sup>the Bichrites assembled and followed him in.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And all the men who were with Joab came and besieged him in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8570N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8570N\"></sup>Abel of Beth-maacah. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8570O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8570O\"></sup>They cast up a mound against the city, and it stood against the rampart, and they were battering the wall to throw it down.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then a wise woman called from the city, “Listen! Listen! Tell Joab, ‘Come here, that I may speak to you.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he came near her, and the woman said, “Are you Joab?” He answered, “I am.” Then she said to him, “Listen to the words of your servant.” And he answered, “I am listening.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then she said, “They used to say in former times, ‘Let them but ask counsel at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8573P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8573P\"></sup>Abel,’ and so they settled a matter.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>I am one of those who are peaceable and faithful in Israel. You seek to destroy a city that is a mother in Israel. Why will you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8574Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8574Q\"></sup>swallow up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8574R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8574R\"></sup>the heritage of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Joab answered, “Far be it from me, far be it, that I should <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8575S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8575S\"></sup>swallow up or destroy!",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>That is not true. But a man of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8576T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8576T\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim, called Sheba the son of Bichri, has lifted up his hand against King David. Give up him alone, and I will withdraw from the city.” And the woman said to Joab, “Behold, his head shall be thrown to you over the wall.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then the woman went to all the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8577U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8577U\"></sup>in her wisdom. And they cut off the head of Sheba the son of Bichri and threw it out to Joab. So he blew the trumpet, and they dispersed from the city, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8577V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8577V\"></sup>every man to his home. And Joab returned to Jerusalem to the king.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8578W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8578W\"></sup>Now Joab was in command of all the army of Israel; and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was in command of the Cherethites and the Pelethites;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8579X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8579X\"></sup>Adoram was in charge of the forced labor; and Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud was the recorder;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and Sheva was secretary; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8580Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8580Y\"></sup>Zadok and Abiathar were priests;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8581Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8581Z\"></sup>Ira the Jairite was also David's priest."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>Now there was a famine in the days of David for three years, year after year. And David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8582A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8582A\"></sup>sought the face of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “There is bloodguilt on Saul and on his house, because he put the Gibeonites to death.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the king called the Gibeonites and spoke to them. Now the Gibeonites were not of the people of Israel but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8583B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8583B\"></sup>of the remnant of the Amorites. Although the people of Israel had sworn to spare them, Saul had sought to strike them down in his zeal for the people of Israel and Judah.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And David said to the Gibeonites, “What shall I do for you? And how shall I make atonement, that you may bless <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8584C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8584C\"></sup>the heritage of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The Gibeonites said to him, “It is not a matter of silver or gold between us and Saul or his house; neither is it for us to put any man to death in Israel.” And he said, “What do you say that I shall do for you?”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They said to the king, “The man who consumed us and planned to destroy us, so that we should have no place in all the territory of Israel,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>let seven of his sons be given to us, so that we may hang them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8587D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8587D\"></sup>Gibeah of Saul, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8587E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8587E\"></sup>the chosen of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And the king said, “I will give them.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But the king spared Mephibosheth, the son of Saul's son Jonathan, because of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8588F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8588F\"></sup>the oath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that was between them, between David and Jonathan the son of Saul.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The king took the two sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8589G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8589G\"></sup>Rizpah the daughter of Aiah, whom she bore to Saul, Armoni and Mephibosheth; and the five sons of Merab the daughter of Saul, whom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8589H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8589H\"></sup>she bore to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8589I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8589I\"></sup>Adriel the son of Barzillai the Meholathite;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and he gave them into the hands of the Gibeonites, and they hanged them on the mountain before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the seven of them perished together. They were put to death in the first days of harvest, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8590J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8590J\"></sup>at the beginning of barley harvest.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8591K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8591K\"></sup>Then Rizpah the daughter of Aiah took sackcloth and spread it for herself on the rock, from the beginning of harvest until rain fell upon them from the heavens. And she did not allow the birds of the air to come upon them by day, or the beasts of the field by night.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When David was told what Rizpah the daughter of Aiah, the concubine of Saul, had done,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>David went and took the bones of Saul and the bones of his son Jonathan from the men of Jabesh-gilead, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8593L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8593L\"></sup>who had stolen them from the public square of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8593M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8593M\"></sup>Beth-shan, where the Philistines had hanged them, on the day the Philistines killed Saul on Gilboa.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And he brought up from there the bones of Saul and the bones of his son Jonathan; and they gathered the bones of those who were hanged.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And they buried the bones of Saul and his son Jonathan in the land of Benjamin in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8595N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8595N\"></sup>Zela, in the tomb of Kish his father. And they did all that the king commanded. And after that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8595O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8595O\"></sup>God responded to the plea for the land.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>There was war again between the Philistines and Israel, and David went down together with his servants, and they fought against the Philistines. And David grew weary.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Ishbi-benob, one of the descendants <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8597P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8597P\"></sup>of the giants, whose spear weighed three hundred shekels of bronze, and who was armed with a new sword, thought to kill David.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But Abishai the son of Zeruiah came to his aid and attacked the Philistine and killed him. Then David's men swore to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8598Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8598Q\"></sup>“You shall no longer go out with us to battle, lest you quench <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8598R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8598R\"></sup>the lamp of Israel.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8599S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8599S\"></sup>After this there was again war with the Philistines at Gob. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8599T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8599T\"></sup>Sibbecai <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8599U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8599U\"></sup>the Hushathite struck down Saph, who was one of the descendants <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8599V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8599V\"></sup>of the giants.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And there was again war with the Philistines at Gob, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8600W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8600W\"></sup>Elhanan the son of Jaare-oregim, the Bethlehemite, struck down Goliath the Gittite, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8600X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8600X\"></sup>the shaft of whose spear was like a weaver's beam.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And there was again war at Gath, where there was a man of great stature, who had six fingers on each hand, and six toes on each foot, twenty-four in number, and he also was descended <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8601Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8601Y\"></sup>from the giants.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8602Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8602Z\"></sup>he taunted Israel, Jonathan the son of Shimei, David's brother, struck him down.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>These four were descended <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8603AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8603AA\"></sup>from the giants in Gath, and they fell by the hand of David and by the hand of his servants."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>And David spoke <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8604A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8604A\"></sup>to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the words of this song on the day when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delivered him from the hand of all his enemies, and from the hand of Saul.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8605B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8605B\"></sup>He said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8605C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8605C\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is my rock and my fortress and my deliverer,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8606D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8606D\"></sup>my God, my rock, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8606E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8606E\"></sup>in whom I take refuge,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8606F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8606F\"></sup>my shield, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8606G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8606G\"></sup>the horn of my salvation,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8606H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8606H\"></sup>my stronghold and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8606I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8606I\"></sup>my refuge,my savior; you save me from violence.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I call upon the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8607J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8607J\"></sup>worthy to be praised,and I am saved from my enemies.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8608K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8608K\"></sup>“For the waves of death encompassed me,the torrents of destruction assailed me;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8609L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8609L\"></sup>the cords of Sheol entangled me;the snares of death confronted me.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8610M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8610M\"></sup>“In my distress I called upon the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;to my God I called.From his temple he heard my voice,and my cry <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8610N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8610N\"></sup>came to his ears.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8611O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8611O\"></sup>the earth reeled and rocked;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8611P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8611P\"></sup>the foundations of the heavens trembledand quaked, because he was angry.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Smoke went up from his nostrils,and devouring fire from his mouth;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8612Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8612Q\"></sup>glowing coals flamed forth from him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8613R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8613R\"></sup>He bowed the heavens and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8613S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8613S\"></sup>came down;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8613T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8613T\"></sup>thick darkness was under his feet.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He rode on a cherub and flew;he was seen on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8614U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8614U\"></sup>the wings of the wind.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8615V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8615V\"></sup>darkness around him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8615W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8615W\"></sup>his canopy,thick clouds, a gathering of water.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Out of the brightness before him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8616X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8616X\"></sup>coals of fire flamed forth.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8617Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8617Y\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> thundered from heaven,and the Most High uttered his voice.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he sent out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8618Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8618Z\"></sup>arrows and scattered them;lightning, and routed them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the channels of the sea were seen;the foundations of the world were laid bare,at the rebuke of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,at the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8619AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8619AA\"></sup>blast of the breath of his nostrils.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8620AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8620AB\"></sup>“He sent from on high, he took me;he drew me out of many waters.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He rescued me from my strong enemy,from those who hated me,for they were too mighty for me.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They confronted me in the day of my calamity,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was my support.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8623AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8623AC\"></sup>He brought me out into a broad place;he rescued me, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8623AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8623AD\"></sup>he delighted in me.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8624AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8624AE\"></sup>dealt with me according to my righteousness;according to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8624AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8624AF\"></sup>cleanness of my hands he rewarded me.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8625AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8625AG\"></sup>For I have kept the ways of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>and have not wickedly departed from my God.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8626AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8626AH\"></sup>For all his rules were before me,and from his statutes I did not turn aside.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>I was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8627AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8627AI\"></sup>blameless before him,and I kept myself from guilt.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8628AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8628AJ\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has rewarded me according to my righteousness,according to my cleanness in his sight.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8629AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8629AK\"></sup>“With the merciful you show yourself merciful;with the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8629AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8629AL\"></sup>blameless man you show yourself blameless;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>with the purified you deal purely,and with the crooked you make yourself seem tortuous.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8631AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8631AM\"></sup>You save a humble people,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8631AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8631AN\"></sup>but your eyes are on the haughty to bring them down.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8632AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8632AO\"></sup>For you are my lamp, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and my God lightens my darkness.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>For by you I can run against a troop,and by my God I can leap over a wall.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>This God—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8634AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8634AP\"></sup>his way is perfect;the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8634AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8634AQ\"></sup>word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> proves true;he is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8634AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8634AR\"></sup>a shield for all those who take refuge in him.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“For who is God, but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8635AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8635AS\"></sup>And who is a rock, except our God?",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>This God is my <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8636AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8636AT\"></sup>strong refugeand has made my way blameless.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8637AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8637AU\"></sup>He made my feet like the feet of a deerand set me secure <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8637AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8637AV\"></sup>on the heights.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8638AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8638AW\"></sup>He trains my hands for war,so that my arms can bend a bow of bronze.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>You have given me the shield of your salvation,and your gentleness made me great.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8640AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8640AX\"></sup>You gave a wide place for my steps under me,and my feet did not slip;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>I pursued my enemies and destroyed them,and did not turn back until they were consumed.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>I consumed them; I thrust them through, so that they did not rise;they fell <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8642AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8642AY\"></sup>under my feet.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>For you equipped me with strength for the battle;you made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8643AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8643AZ\"></sup>those who rise against me sink under me.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8644BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8644BA\"></sup>made my enemies turn their backs to me,those who hated me, and I destroyed them.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>They looked, but there was none to save;they cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8645BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8645BB\"></sup>he did not answer them.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>I beat them fine <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8646BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8646BC\"></sup>as the dust of the earth;I crushed them and stamped them down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8646BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8646BD\"></sup>like the mire of the streets.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>“You delivered me from strife with my people;you kept me as the head of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8647BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8647BE\"></sup>the nations;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8647BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8647BF\"></sup>people whom I had not known served me.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Foreigners came cringing to me;as soon as they heard of me, they obeyed me.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Foreigners lost heartand came trembling <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8649BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8649BG\"></sup>out of their fortresses.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, and blessed be my rock,and exalted be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8650BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8650BH\"></sup>my God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8650BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8650BI\"></sup>the rock of my salvation,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>the God who gave me vengeanceand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8651BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8651BJ\"></sup>brought down peoples under me,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>who brought me out from my enemies;you exalted me above <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8652BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8652BK\"></sup>those who rose against me;you delivered me from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8652BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8652BL\"></sup>men of violence.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8653BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8653BM\"></sup>“For this I will praise you, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, among the nations,and sing praises to your name.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8654BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8654BN\"></sup>Great salvation he brings to his king,and shows steadfast love to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8654BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8654BO\"></sup>his anointed,to David and his offspring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8654BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8654BP\"></sup>forever.”"
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>Now these are the last words of David:The oracle of David, the son of Jesse,the oracle of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8655A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8655A\"></sup>the man who was raised on high,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8655B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8655B\"></sup>the anointed of the God of Jacob,the sweet psalmist of Israel:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8656C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8656C\"></sup>“The Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> speaks by me;his word is on my tongue.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The God of Israel has spoken;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8657D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8657D\"></sup>the Rock of Israel has said to me:When one rules justly over men,ruling <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8657E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8657E\"></sup>in the fear of God,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8658F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8658F\"></sup>dawns on them like the morning light,like the sun shining forth on a cloudless morning,like rain that makes grass to sprout from the earth.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“For does not my house stand so with God?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8659G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8659G\"></sup>For he has made with me an everlasting covenant,ordered in all things and secure.For will he not cause to prosperall my help and my desire?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But worthless men are all like thorns that are thrown away,for they cannot be taken with the hand;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>but the man who touches themarms himself with iron and the shaft of a spear,and they are utterly consumed with fire.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8662H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8662H\"></sup>These are the names of the mighty men whom David had: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8662I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8662I\"></sup>Josheb-basshebeth a Tahchemonite; he was chief of the three. He wielded his spear against eight hundred whom he killed at one time.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And next to him among the three mighty men was Eleazar the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8663J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8663J\"></sup>Dodo, son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8663K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8663K\"></sup>Ahohi. He was with David when they defied the Philistines who were gathered there for battle, and the men of Israel withdrew.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He rose and struck down the Philistines until his hand was weary, and his hand clung to the sword. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought about a great victory that day, and the men returned after him only to strip the slain.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And next to him was Shammah, the son of Agee the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8665L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8665L\"></sup>Hararite. The Philistines gathered together at Lehi, where there was a plot of ground full of lentils, and the men fled from the Philistines.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But he took his stand in the midst of the plot and defended it and struck down the Philistines, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> worked a great victory.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And three of the thirty chief men went down and came about harvest time to David at the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8667M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8667M\"></sup>cave of Adullam, when a band of Philistines was encamped <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8667N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8667N\"></sup>in the Valley of Rephaim.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>David was then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8668O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8668O\"></sup>in the stronghold, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8668P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8668P\"></sup>the garrison of the Philistines was then at Bethlehem.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And David said longingly, “Oh, that someone would give me water to drink from the well of Bethlehem that is by the gate!”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the three mighty men broke through the camp of the Philistines and drew water out of the well of Bethlehem that was by the gate and carried and brought it to David. But he would not drink of it. He poured it out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and said, “Far be it from me, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that I should do this. Shall I drink <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8671Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8671Q\"></sup>the blood of the men who went at the risk of their lives?” Therefore he would not drink it. These things the three mighty men did.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now Abishai, the brother of Joab, the son of Zeruiah, was chief of the thirty. And he wielded his spear against three hundred men and killed them and won a name beside the three.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He was the most renowned of the thirty and became their commander, but he did not attain to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8673R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8673R\"></sup>the three.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8674S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8674S\"></sup>Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was a valiant man of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8674T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8674T\"></sup>Kabzeel, a doer of great deeds. He struck down two ariels of Moab. He also went down and struck down a lion in a pit on a day when snow had fallen.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And he struck down an Egyptian, a handsome man. The Egyptian had a spear in his hand, but Benaiah went down to him with a staff and snatched the spear out of the Egyptian's hand and killed him with his own spear.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>These things did Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and won a name beside the three mighty men.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He was renowned among the thirty, but he did not attain to the three. And David set him over his bodyguard.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8678U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8678U\"></sup>Asahel the brother of Joab was one of the thirty; Elhanan the son of Dodo of Bethlehem,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8679V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8679V\"></sup>Shammah of Harod, Elika of Harod,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Helez the Paltite, Ira the son of Ikkesh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8680W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8680W\"></sup>of Tekoa,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Abiezer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8681X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8681X\"></sup>of Anathoth, Mebunnai <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8681Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8681Y\"></sup>the Hushathite,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Zalmon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8682Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8682Z\"></sup>the Ahohite, Maharai <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8682AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8682AA\"></sup>of Netophah,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Heleb the son of Baanah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8683AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8683AB\"></sup>of Netophah, Ittai the son of Ribai of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8683AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8683AC\"></sup>Gibeah of the people of Benjamin,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Benaiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8684AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8684AD\"></sup>of Pirathon, Hiddai of the brooks of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8684AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8684AE\"></sup>Gaash,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Abi-albon the Arbathite, Azmaveth of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8685AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8685AF\"></sup>Bahurim,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Eliahba the Shaalbonite, the sons of Jashen, Jonathan,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8687AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8687AG\"></sup>Shammah the Hararite, Ahiam the son of Sharar the Hararite,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Eliphelet the son of Ahasbai <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8688AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8688AH\"></sup>of Maacah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8688AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8688AI\"></sup>Eliam the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8688AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8688AJ\"></sup>Ahithophel the Gilonite,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Hezro <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8689AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8689AK\"></sup>of Carmel, Paarai the Arbite,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Igal the son of Nathan <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8690AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8690AL\"></sup>of Zobah, Bani the Gadite,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8691AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8691AM\"></sup>of Beeroth, the armor-bearer of Joab the son of Zeruiah,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8692AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8692AN\"></sup>Ira the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8692AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8692AO\"></sup>Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8693AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8693AP\"></sup>Uriah the Hittite: thirty-seven in all."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8694A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8694A\"></sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8694B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8694B\"></sup>Again the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was kindled against Israel, and he incited David against them, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8694C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8694C\"></sup>“Go, number Israel and Judah.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the king said to Joab, the commander of the army, who was with him, “Go through all the tribes of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8695D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8695D\"></sup>from Dan to Beersheba, and number the people, that I may know the number of the people.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Joab said to the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8696E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8696E\"></sup>“May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God add to the people a hundred times as many as they are, while the eyes of my lord the king still see it, but why does my lord the king delight in this thing?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the king's word prevailed against Joab and the commanders of the army. So Joab and the commanders of the army went out from the presence of the king to number the people of Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They crossed the Jordan and began from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8698F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8698F\"></sup>Aroer, and from the city that is in the middle of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8698G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8698G\"></sup>valley, toward Gad and on to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8698H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8698H\"></sup>Jazer.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then they came to Gilead, and to Kadesh in the land of the Hittites; and they came to Dan, and from Dan they went around to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8699I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8699I\"></sup>Sidon,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and came to the fortress of Tyre and to all the cities of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8700J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8700J\"></sup>Hivites and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8700K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8700K\"></sup>Canaanites; and they went out to the Negeb of Judah at Beersheba.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So when they had gone through all the land, they came to Jerusalem at the end of nine months and twenty days.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Joab gave the sum of the numbering of the people to the king: in Israel there were 800,000 valiant men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8702L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8702L\"></sup>who drew the sword, and the men of Judah were 500,000.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8703M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8703M\"></sup>David's heart struck him after he had numbered the people. And David said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8703N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8703N\"></sup>“I have sinned greatly in what I have done. But now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, please take away the iniquity of your servant, for I have done <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8703O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8703O\"></sup>very foolishly.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And when David arose in the morning, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8704P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8704P\"></sup>the prophet Gad, David's <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8704Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8704Q\"></sup>seer, saying,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Go and say to David, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, Three things I offer you. Choose one of them, that I may do it to you.’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Gad came to David and told him, and said to him, “Shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8706R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8706R\"></sup>three years of famine come to you in your land? Or will you flee three months before your foes while they pursue you? Or shall there be three days' pestilence in your land? Now consider, and decide what answer I shall return to him who sent me.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then David said to Gad, “I am in great distress. Let us fall into the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8707S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8707S\"></sup>for his mercy is great; but let me not fall into the hand of man.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8708T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8708T\"></sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent a pestilence on Israel from the morning until the appointed time. And there died of the people from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8708U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8708U\"></sup>Dan to Beersheba 70,000 men.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8709V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8709V\"></sup>the angel stretched out his hand toward Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8709W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8709W\"></sup>to destroy it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8709X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8709X\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> relented from the calamity and said to the angel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8709Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8709Y\"></sup>who was working destruction among the people, “It is enough; now stay your hand.” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8709Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8709Z\"></sup>the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was by the threshing floor of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8709AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8709AA\"></sup>Araunah the Jebusite.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then David spoke to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> when he saw the angel who was striking the people, and said, “Behold, I have sinned, and I have done wickedly. But these sheep, what have they done? Please let your hand be against me and against my father's house.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Gad came that day to David and said to him, “Go up, raise an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the threshing floor of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8711AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8711AB\"></sup>Araunah the Jebusite.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So David went up at Gad's word, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And when Araunah looked down, he saw the king and his servants coming on toward him. And Araunah went out and paid homage to the king with his face to the ground.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Araunah said, “Why has my lord the king come to his servant?” David said, “To buy the threshing floor from you, in order to build an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that the plague <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8714AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8714AC\"></sup>may be averted from the people.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Araunah said to David, “Let my lord the king take and offer up what seems good to him. Here are the oxen for the burnt offering and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8715AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8715AD\"></sup>threshing sledges and the yokes of the oxen for the wood.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>All this, O king, Araunah gives to the king.” And Araunah said to the king, “May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8716AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8716AE\"></sup>accept you.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But the king said to Araunah, “No, but I will buy it from you for a price. I will not offer burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God that cost me nothing.” So David bought the threshing floor and the oxen for fifty shekels of silver.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And David built there an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-8718AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-8718AF\"></sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> responded to the plea for the land, and the plague was averted from Israel."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;